title: mexican salad
directions: Put dressing over salad and mix good just before serving. Stir in Fritos last.
Serve with Mexican casserole.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Season chicken breasts with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Wrap each chicken breast with 2 slices bacon.
(Chicken may set covered overnight at this point, if desired.)
Dice onion and cook in 2 tablespoons butter over low heat until onion is translucent. Mix in sour cream, mushrooms and soup.
Broil bacon wrapped chicken for 5 to 10 minutes or until bacon is slightly brown on both sides of chicken.
Cover chicken with sauce mixture and bake in tightly covered 9 x 13-inch baking pan at 250° for 3 hours. Bake longer if there is a greater quantity in the recipe.
May leave cover off the last 15 minutes of baking to brown.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1 cup of pecans.
Shape into ball.
Roll in the reserved pecans; chill until ready to serve.
Serve with assorted crackers of your choice.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Add sugar gradually and then vanilla.
When blended, add flour that has been sifted together with baking power and salt.
Fold in egg whites that have been whipped until stiff, but not dry.

title: henry bain sauce
directions: Lightly blend chutney in blender.
Mix well with other ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Pour over cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.
Also enhances beef.

title: dip for cakes
directions: Mix flour with melted butter.
Add water and sugar with a pinch of salt.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.

title: orange blossom punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, ice cream and sherbet.
Mix at low speed in electric mixer until blended.
To serve, add ginger ale and stir to blend.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: chicken landoff
directions: Place boned and skinned chicken (6) whole breasts in bottom of baking dish.
Cover each breast with slice of Swiss cheese.
Mix one can of cream of mushroom soup with 1/2 cup of wine or ginger ale.
Pour over chicken.
Mix one stick of butter with the stuffing mix.
Sprinkle over top; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: biscuit pizzas
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage together.
Drain fat.
Take muffin tin and spray with Pam.
Flatten biscuits with your hands and place in muffin cup.
Biscuits should come up approximately halfway in muffin cup.
Place 1 tablespoon of pizza sauce inside biscuits.
Fill biscuits with your favorite pizza topping, such as pepperoni, mushrooms, hamburger and sausage.
Fill them full because biscuits will rise around the meat.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: ryan's quick good-as-gold chili
directions: Heat oil in large skillet until hot.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time.
Cook until golden brown, about 5 minutes on each side.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Cool slightly; cut into 1/4-inch cubes and set aside.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons oil from skillet; heat oil until hot.
Add onion and garlic; cook and stir about 5 minutes or until golden.
Add remaining ingredients and chicken.
Mix well.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens slightly.
Garnish as desired.
Enjoy!

title: marinated meat balls
directions: Heat mixture and cover meat balls in Pyrex bowl.
Keep hot.

title: new years cookies
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Warm milk.
Add remaining ingredients and enough flour to make a soft dough you can beat with a spoon.
Let rise until doubled.
Add 1 tablespoon at a time to hot oil.
Fry until brown and roll in sugar.

title: gourmet beef tenderloin
directions: Rub tenderloin with butter.
Combine Mein Yen with caraway seed and pat on sides of meat.
Insert meat thermometer and cook at 300° until the temperature is 150° (about 1 1/2 hours).
Saute mushrooms and spoon over top before serving.
Serve beside wild rice.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter; pour sweetened Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.
Sprinkle with chips, then coconut and nuts.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until light brown.
Cool; chill thoroughly if desired. Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes 36 bars.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Mix together and bring to a boil the sugar, raisins and water.
Boil 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Add shortening.
Add dry and creamed mixture together.
Add vanilla. Bake in square dish at 350°.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Check at mid-way.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix soup, Cheddar cheese, milk, mayonnaise and egg.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: great meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, Karo and maple syrup.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add vanilla and salt.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for approximately 50 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Fry ground beef and onion until brown.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer mashed potatoes on top of beef.
Layer corn on top of potatoes.
Put butter on top of corn.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch pan in oven. Stir tortillas into oleo until tortillas are coated.
Combine onion, soups, chilies and chicken; mix well.
Pour over tortillas; stir well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Garnish with cheese and lettuce.
Yields 6 servings.

title: indonesian cabbage
directions: Melt the oleo in skillet. Add the onion, chopped, and saute until tender. Stir in eggs, one at a time. Chop the cabbage and add to the mixture. Cover and simmer until tender. Season to taste.

title: onion rings
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Cover with buttermilk and allow to stand for 1 hour.
Put flour in a plastic paper bag. Add onions in bag and shake until onion rings are coated with flour.
Fry in hot grease.
Drain on paper towel.

title: easy coconut bars
directions: Mix together margarine and graham cracker crumbs and pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix condensed milk and coconut.
Spread on top of graham cracker base and bake for an additional 15 minutes at 325°.
Pour chocolate chips on top of coconut mixture.
Return to oven only until chips are melted. Spread to smooth over top.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour in 2 regular pie crusts. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: nut burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into patties.
Either saute in 1 tablespoon canola oil or bake on greased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes, turning halfway through cooking time.
Makes 4 to 6 patties.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 2 ounces of the cheese and 1/2 can of fried onions.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.
Then top with remaining cheese and onions, return to oven until cheese has melted.
Serves 6.

title: salade nicoise
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender, but not mushy, about 10 minutes.
When cool enough to handle, quarter the potatoes and transfer them to a large bowl.
Add green beans, tomatoes, onion, olives, parsley, a pinch of salt and the pepper. Pour 1/2 cup of the Vinaigrette over vegetables and toss gently but well.

title: texas beans
directions: Brown bacon and hamburger (or sausage). Mix remaining ingredients into meat mixture. Bake in casserole or small roaster for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef brisket
directions: Trim excess fat from brisket.
Punch holes in brisket and place in roasting pan.
Pour coffee over brisket and add Lipton onion soup mix over brisket.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Cook for 5 hours in 350° oven.
When cooked, remove from oven.
Cool and slice.
Place in baking dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over it and bake 1 hour.

title: glorified rice
directions: Combine hot rice, sugar and marshmallows.
Let cool.
Add pineapple and whipped cream.
Put cherries on top and chill.

title: glazed kiwifruit flan
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and melted butter; press into flan dish. Whip the cream until it begins to hold shape. Sprinkle with instant pudding and continue beating until mixture holds. Fold in sherry. Spoon the creamed mixture into the flan dish and smooth top. Arrange the sliced kiwifruit over the top in a circle. In a small glass dish, heat lemon juice and jam on High in microwave 1.5 minutes. Strain and allow to cool a little before pouring over the fruit. Chill well before serving.

title: burnt leather cake
directions: Burn 1 cup sugar in heavy cast-iron skillet until light in color and
it
foams.
Very,
very	slowly,
add
1 cup hot water. Stir
until
sugar dissolves and cool (1/2 cup of this is used for
cake).
Cream	sugar
and
butter together.
Add yolks of eggs;
mix well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Place meat in slow-cooking pot; cover with sliced onion. Combine garlic, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, salt, paprika and mustard.
Stir in water and pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low for 9 to 10 hours.
Turn control to high.
Dissolve flour in small amount of cold water and stir into meat mixture. Cook on high for 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly thickened. Serve goulash over noodles or rice.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: jollof rice
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Brown chicken in frying pan in hot oil.
Then put the browned chicken in a large heavy pot.
Using same frying pan that you browned chicken in, add onion, pork and any other cubes of meat.
Fry lightly and add to large pot with chicken.
Add seasonings, water and tomato paste to large pot.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Clean and wash rice.
Add to meat mixture.
Stir well and cook slow, 35 to 45 minutes.
Hot pepper optional.

title: pear salad
directions: Arrange pear halves on bed of lettuce leaves.
Fill each center with heaping tablespoonful of Miracle Whip.
Sprinkle generously with shredded cheese.
Serve chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Layer the cucumber slices on paper towels.
Put a heavy plate on the cucumber to take the excess water out of the cucumbers, about 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, add all the ingredient except paprika.
Mix well and add the cucumber slices.
Chill overnight. Before serving sprinkle paprika over.
Take out the garlic chunks. Can be doubled or tripled.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Mix together until smooth the cream cheese, mayonnaise, cheese, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Place trimmed bread between wax paper and roll with rolling pin until flat. Spread cheese mixture on bread and roll with asparagus stalk in center.
(I use cut asparagus.)
Brush with melted butter and bake, seam side down, at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
To brown tops, turn broiler on for last few minutes.

title: joan's baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour onion soup mix and cream of mushroom soup over chicken.
Add 1/2 cup of water.
Cook in a 375° oven until done.

title: chicken ignolia
directions: Place chicken pieces skin side up in baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Pour oil over chicken.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Baste occasionally with pan drippings.
Pour the drippings over the chicken just before serving.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients and put in baked pie shell.
Chill overnight or at least 4 hours before serving. Graham cracker crust is also good.

title: grilled minted lemon chicken
directions: In a small bowl, mix together the lemon rind, lemon juice, mint, honey, soy sauce, salt and pepper until well blended. Preheat the broiler or grill; arrange breast halves on tray or broiler pan and brush liberally with 2/3 of the sauce.
Grill the chicken on each side, 7 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: cheese ball
directions: Bring ingredients to room temperature.
Mix well.
Form ball and roll in nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put dry ingredients in mixing bowl and stir.
Add raisins and stir.
Add egg and shortening and stir. Gradually add buttermilk until you have a firm, but not stiff, dough (like a biscuit dough).
Put on a lightly floured board and knead for about 2 minutes until dough becomes smooth.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased loaf pan or small loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: chocolate peppermint dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, except stir 1 teaspoon mint extract into batter.
Pour into pan.
Bake as directed.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely. Cut cake crosswise into halves.

title: spinach dip
directions: *May use blended tofu or imitation sour cream.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cook slowly, stirring constantly.
Brown two pie shells.
Pour mixture into shells; let cool.
Prepare meringue and brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook until hot butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Add white sauce and cook until thickened.
Cook the macaroni, then drain.
Pour into a dish (casserole dish).
Mix in the Cheez Whiz, then mix in the white sauce.
(Optional:
Put cheese slices on top.)
Put in oven at 250° until cheese melts or heat in microwave for 5 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: chili burger supper
directions: Following package directions, cook macaroni.
Drain thoroughly.
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add chili beef soup and tomato soup.
Add spaghetti or macaroni.
Heat mixture, stirring occasionally for 5 to 7 minutes or until the mixture is bubbly.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift together cocoa, flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Cream together shortening, margarine, eggs and sugar, mixing well.
Add dry ingredients to mixture, then add milk and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine the first 3 ingredients; blend at low speed until crumbly.
Stir in nuts. Press 2 3/4 cups crumb mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
To remaining mixture, add cinnamon, soda, salt, sour cream, vanilla and egg; blend well.
Stir in apples.
Spoon evenly over base. Bake for 25 to 35 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cut into squares.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Makes 12 to 15 squares.

title: spaghetti dinner
directions: Place fat (if needed) in frying pan.
Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain in colander; run hot water over mixture to remove all fat.
Return to skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and cover.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Turn off for at least 15 minutes.
Do not remove cover while cooking on stored heat.

title: melon cooler
directions: Cut melon in half lengthwise; scoop out seeds and drain well. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cubes and stir until gelatin begins to thicken, about 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Stir in banana.
Place melon halves in small bowls; spoon in gelatin mixture.
(Chill any excess fruited gelatin in a dessert dish.)
Chill until firm.
Cut in wedges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: reuben's dip pot
directions: Cut 1/2-inch slice from top of loaf and reserve.
Using sharp knife, remove bread inside loaf, leaving 1/2-inch thick shell. Cut bread into 1 1/4-inch cubes.
Combine butter and oil; brush on cubes.
Brown cubes in broiler 6 inches from heat, or in toaster oven, stirring until uniformly colored.
Set aside.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Separate large cabbage leaves and wilt with boiling water.
Spread 2 tablespoons of meat mixture on each leaf.
Roll up, tucking in sides of leaf and pin with toothpicks.
Place in large pot with one cup of water.
Pour the following over cabbage rolls: 1 can tomatoes (large) and 1 can of tomato sauce.
Cook slowly, about an hour.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Combine all other ingredients.
Add yeast to mixture.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix according to package directions. Bake in a greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan for 15 minutes at the temperature specified on the cake mix box.

title: under the sea pear salad
directions: Drain pears and reserve 3/4 cup of syrup.
Dice pears and set aside.
Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add pear syrup and lemon juice.
Measure 1 1/4 cups of gelatin into a small jello mold.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken in 3 cups water until tender, using pressure cooker or any kind of pot.
Remove from stock.
Take off the bones.
Cut up chicken (not too fine).
Cook spaghetti (the real Italian kind is less starchy) in chicken for 9 minutes.
Boil pepper in a little salted water after it is cut in small pieces. Cut pimiento.
Mix all ingredients except the almonds.
Arrange in Pyrex or casserole dishes.
Sprinkle sliced almonds on top and heat in slow oven for an hour before serving.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in large iron skillet. While butter is melting, mix sugar, flour and milk and pour over butter. Dump can of peaches and syrup all in center. Cook at 375° until brown on top. Crust will rise to the top. This can also be made in a casserole dish.

title: just like fried ice cream
directions: Using a large ice cream scoop, make four 1/2 cup scoops of ice cream. Place in a shallow pan. Cover and store in the freezer until firm.

title: taco pie
directions: Grease pie pan.
Cook beef and onion; add seasonings, spread in pan.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth.
Pour over beef, bake at 400° for
25 minutes.
Melt cheese.
Serve with lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: microwave fudge pie(fast and good for unexpected folks that just drop in.)
directions: Melt butter and put in mixing bowl.
Add sugar and beat well. Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour, melted chocolate, vanilla and pecans.
Spray 9-inch pie plate with Pam.
Place filling in pie plate.
Microwave on high 6 minutes, giving pie a half turn after 3 minutes.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat; drain. Combine all ingredients (don't drain juices off of cans) except cheese and chips into crock-pot. Cook until warmed through. Serve with chips and cheese.

title: sangria
directions: Boil the water, sugar and cinnamon for 5 minutes and let the syrup cool. Cut the lemon, bananas and orange into slices and cover with the cooled syrup. Chill the mixture for several hours. Add ice, sliced fruit, 1/2 cup syrup and red wine. Stir the mixture thoroughly, mashing the fruit slightly. Serve the Sangria in well chilled glasses, garnishing each glass with some of the fruit.

title: broccoli pizza
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spread pizza dough into pan. Cover with shredded sharp Cheddar cheese. Season cooked broccoli with a little oil, salt and garlic powder.
Simmer until nice and warm. Add broccoli over Cheddar cheese. Add grated cheese and sprinkle with bacon bits.
Bake approximately 30 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Remove from oven and add Mozzarella cheese to cover entire top of pizza.
Return to oven until cheese is completely melted and bubbly. Serve hot or cold.

title: low-fat vegetable scallop saute
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat.
Add wine and all vegetables except onion.
Saute, stirring frequently, until vegetables are tender, but still crunchy (3 to 5 minutes).
Add scallops, dill and onion.
Cook until scallop flesh turns opaque (5 to 10 minutes).
Serve with rice, green vegetables or tossed salad.

title: apricot cream cheese drops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheet. Cream the Crisco, cream cheese and milk in a medium bowl. Beat in brown sugar, combined flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix in creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts. Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet.
Place 2-inches apart. Bake for 14 minutes.

title: dream cake
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then mix vinegar and Miracle Whip together and pour over corn mixture.
Mix well.
Chill and serve. This is a great "mix ahead" dish for potluck dinners or salad luncheons.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use a casserole dish.
Layer 1/2 bag of chips on bottom of pan.
Remove chicken from bone.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes with onion and chicken.
Layer over chips.
Put cheese over mixture and put a layer of chips over soup and chicken mix.
Add more cheese over chips, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: german chocolate cheese cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
In another bowl, whip the softened cream cheese, sugar and eggs.
Pour 1/2 of batter into 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Pour cream cheese mixture slowly on top and then pour rest of cake mix over the cream cheese mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
On top (each serving) put dollop of whipped cream and maraschino cherry.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Note:
You may use orange or pineapple cake mix.

title: arli's broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Cut broccoli heads into flowerets and mix with the bacon, pecans, raisins and onion. Just before serving, pour on the dressing made of mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Chop corned beef into small pieces. Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Chill for 2 hours. Shape into a ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry sunrise papaya bread with macadamia nuts
directions: Beat papaya pulp, oil, eggs and sugar at low speed of electric mixer for a few minutes.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Add nuts.
Combine with liquid mixture and stir until well blended.
Pour into a 4 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until done.
Freezes well.

title: easy pasta primavera
directions: Boil water and cook pasta.
In separate pan, heat olive oil and garlic.
Toss bag of frozen vegetables and heat through.
Mix milk with can of soup; stir with vegetables.
Mix in 1/2 can of onion rings.
Add white and black peppers.
Cook vegetables as desired.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and shape into balls. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Shred cheese and place on top of bread. Sprinkle sausage over cheese. Mix 2 1/4 cups milk, mustard and eggs together and pour over casserole. Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Mix the soup with 1/2 cup milk and pour over casserole. Cook 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Serves 8.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into 2 loaves. Wrap in foil.
Let set in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Unwrap and bake on cookie sheet 1 hour at 300°, then turn over and bake 30 minutes more.

title: curried cauliflower, potatoes and beans
directions: Cook/saut onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add spices.
Add 2 cups of water and potatoes.
Bring to boiling.
Turn to simmer and cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Add cauliflower and beans. Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Serve with cilantro.

title: japanese pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: basil pesto sauce
directions: Put all in blender and blend until smooth.
Heat or serve cool over angel hair pasta.

title: pineapple rice pie
directions: Cook rice with salt.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into 3 greased aluminum pans (small square ones).
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour, or until centers are set.

title: my favorite drop dumplings
directions: Mix together and drop by spoonfuls into boiling water.
Cover tightly and cook 10 to 14 minutes.
Good in chicken broth or kraut.
Makes good ones!!

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Add the mayo until it mixes smoothly. Chop up onion, green pepper and tomatoes.
Add to the macaroni. Blend until it's mixed together.
Add the shrimp, salt and pepper and mix thoroughly.
Chill until served.
Better if chilled overnight.

title: peg's banana nut bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Mix remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Pour into greased, floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly except tomato sauce and bacon. Put in meat loaf pan and top with the bacon. Pour tomato sauce over all. Bake in preheated 350° oven about 1 hour. Good!

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat in 1/8-inch strips.
Mix next 3 ingredients together. Roll meat in flour to coat.
Brown in oil mixture.
Add 1 cup or more of water.
Simmer until tender.
Add vegetables until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: In glass measuring cup or small microwavable bowl, microwave chocolate on High for 1 minute.
Stir and microwave 30 seconds. Add cocoa and stir until all chocolate is melted.

title: oven-fried chicken(low fat calorie cholesterol)
directions: Combine water and salt in large bowl; add chicken pieces. Cover and chill 8 hours.
Drain chicken; rinse with cold water, and pat dry.
Place chicken in a shallow dish; pour buttermilk over chicken, turning pieces to coat.
Combine corn flake crumbs and next 5 ingredients in a large heavy-duty, zip-top plastic bake.
Place 2 pieces chicken in bag; seal.
Shake to coat completely.
Remove chicken and repeat procedure with remaining pieces.
Place coated chicken, bone side down in a 15 x 10 x 1 inch jellyroll pan coated with cooking spray, and spray chicken with cooking spray.
Place pan on the lowest rack in oven.
Bake, uncovered at 400° for 45 minutes (do not turn).
Yield: 7 servings.

title: cheese balls
directions: *Whipped cream cheese can be used; just be more generous.

title: spinach and strawberry salad
directions: Tear spinach into bite size pieces.
Scatter with fresh strawberries.

title: rainbow pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and cool. Mix other ingredients and add to cooled pasta. Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Place hamburger, uncooked, in 3-quart baking dish.
Top with thinly sliced carrots.

title: tuna sunshine salad
directions: Gently toss all ingredients.
Cover and chill.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream
the
shortening	and
sugar.
Add
eggs one at a time. Sift the flour;
measure.
Add soda; sift 3 times.	Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, bananas and nuts, if desired.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: coca cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Heat butter, cocoa, marshmallows and Coke until marshmallows melt.
Pour over flour mixture; mix thoroughly.
Beat together buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla; add to flour mixture and mix well.
This batter will be a thin batter. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute the bacon in a saucepan until crisp; drain on paper toweling.
Add onion to 3 tablespoons of the bacon drippings. Saute until the onion is tender, then add corn, pepper, salt, milk and cream.
Simmer (do not boil) for 15 minutes.
Crumble bacon into soup.
Serve very hot.
Garnish with popcorn, if you wish. Yields about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in medium bowl using wire whisk until smooth. Stir in lemon peel and juice. Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the Cool Whip. Spread evenly in bottom of crust.
Press strawberry halves into cream cheese layer, reserving enough for garnish.
Pour 2
cups milk into a large bowl. Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
Let stand 1 minute or until thickened.
Gently stir in 1 cup Cool Whip. Spoon over strawberries in crust. Refrigerate 4 hours. Garnish with remaining Cool Whip and strawberry halves.

title: boiled beef international(to be made the day before using)
directions: Dissolve bouillon in the boiling water; add all ingredients (except beef).
Bring to a boil.
When boiling, add the beef and simmer until fork-tender, 3 to 4 hours.
Chill meat in the broth overnight; skim off any fat.
Next day, reheat.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine tomatoes, oregano and salt.
In greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan, place layer of potatoes and onion. Top with half of tomatoes and 1/4 cup cheese.
Repeat layers. Drizzle with olive oil.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until fork-tender.
If potatoes become dry during baking, add 1/2 cup of water.

title: milk bread
directions: Heat milk and shortening; cool.
In a large bowl, dissolve yeast.
Stir in 1/4 cup sugar from measurement and 1/2 cup warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add sugar, salt, flour, mashed potatoes and milk to yeast mixture.
Blend all together.
(Dough will be stiff.)
Knead on floured board until smooth and elastic, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Put dough in oiled bowl and cover.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch dough down again.
When full, shape into breads.
Place in oiled pans in warm place and let rise until full.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sunday layered salad
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, layer all ingredients in order given.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Do not toss. Cut into squares to serve.
Will keep for several days.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Grease (spray) a 9-inch tube pan with removable bottom.
In a small bowl, mix chopped nuts, cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar.

title: clam fritters
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a mixing bowl; mix well. Combine flour and baking powder; add to clam mixture and stir until moistened.
Heat 3/4-inch oil in a skillet to 350°.
Drop clam mixture into hot oil by level tablespoonfuls.
Fry until light golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.

title: blond brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and cut in squares.

title: zucchini bundt cake
directions: Put oil, zucchini and eggs in blender to mix.
Pour blended ingredients into a bowl and add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a Bundt pan and bake at 350° for about 70 minutes.
(You can bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan or as cupcakes.)

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain clams and pour juice over cut up vegetables.
Add enough water to barely cover top of vegetables.
Cook until tender (20 minutes).

title: granny's pecan cake
directions: Cream eggs, butter and sugar, then add flour and vanilla. Batter should be stiff.
Add pecans.
Pour in tube pan or loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown.
Test with toothpick.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together.
Use 1 to 2 tablespoons per cup.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Set aside.
Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add poppy seed filling and beat until blended.
Beat in egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and sour cream; beat just until blended.
Stir flour, baking soda and salt until mixed and add to poppy mixture gradually, beating well after each addition.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions; add 1 1/2 cups coconut and bake in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
When cake is baked, punch holes while hot and pour cream of coconut over cake.
Let cool.

title: sugarless fruit nut muffins
directions: In saucepan, combine dates, raisins, prunes and water.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Stir in margarine and salt; set aside to cool.
Add remaining ingredients to fruit and stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into greased mini muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberries jamaica
directions: Combine first four ingredients, cover and chill.
Serve with strawberries.
Yields 2 1/3 cups.

title: easy stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half (2 halves per person).
Blanch peppers for 3 minutes.
Drain.
Brown turkey meat.
Add and cook onions until soft.
Mix remaining ingredients, except tomato sauce.
Fill peppers.
Top with tomato sauce and cover with foil.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix and press in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; bake at 350° until flaky, 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and canned milk for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the marshmallows, cocoa and oats.
Mix.
Drop by rounded teaspoon on wax paper.

title: lemon angel pie
directions: Beat eggs; add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Add sugar and beat until glossy.
Grease pie pans.
Put mixture into pans and shape like crust with a spoon.
Bake 1 hour at 250°. Cool.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Spread crushed pineapple with juice in 9x13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with yellow cake mix, and chopped nuts.
Slice margarine, placing over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 min.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: microwave-my version of stuffed peppers
directions: Fry turkey with salt, pepper and onion until browned.
Add the creamed corn; mix.
Fill green peppers.
Put in microwave container.
Mix soup with water and pour over top.
Sprinkle on the sugar.
Cook on High for 15 to 20 minutes, covered.

title: chef dressing
directions: Mash garlic.
Add all other ingredients and with wire whip, whip until thoroughly blended.
Sprinkle a little celery seed on salad.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
In another bowl, mix shortening and sugar with a spoon until soft.
Add eggs and beat well, then add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Add bananas, nuts and dates and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a preheated oven.

title: carrot balls
directions: Combine carrots, bread crumbs and cheese.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Add seasonings.
Form into 10 balls.
Roll in finely crushed Corn Flakes.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Steam cabbage until leaves are bendable.
(Take layers of leaves off head while steaming, about every 5 to 10 minutes.)
Mix rest of ingredients together except tomatoes, soup and bay leaf. Fill each leaf with filling.
Fold like a diaper; secure with toothpick.
Put aside.
Use water from steaming cabbage; add tomatoes and tomato soup.
Put layer of broken cabbage or small pieces into bottom of a large pot (this stops the cabbage rolls from burning).
Add all the rolls and bring to a boil, then reduce to medium heat for about 2 hours.

title: grandma's pound cake
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add (mix in) soft butter, sugar, vanilla, almond extract and salt.
Add flour and milk. Beat for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate sandwich dessert
directions: Crush the Oreo cookies and put in a buttered 9 x 12-inch pan, reserving 3/4 to 1 cup for top.

title: beer bread
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Add beer and egg.
Don't knead or use metal bowl.
Dough will be sticky.
Put in greased loaf pan and let rise 2 hours.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cracker chicken in a pot
directions: Cook all ingredients, except eggs and flour, in pressure cooker for 10 minutes.
Remove chicken from bone and return to broth.
Add eggs, then flour to thicken gravy.
Serve over rice or biscuits.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Whip egg whites and sugar until stiff; gently stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn off heated oven.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto tinfoil on cookie sheet and leave in oven overnight.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine flour, sugar, egg and vinegar.
Boil for 5 minutes, until mixture becomes very thick; chill for one hour.

title: cheery cherry cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat cheese until light and fluffy. Add sweetened condensed milk and blend thoroughly. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill at least 3 hours or until set.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Place chicken in casserole dish. Mix other ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Place on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt, soda, and sugar together.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast water.
Work dough lightly.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Bake at 450° for 10-15 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix together zucchini, onions, sweet peppers, and salt.
Let set overnight, rinse, drain and grind up.
Mix vinegar, sugar, cornstarch and spices.
Cook to thicken.
When syrup is thickened, add ground vegetables, mix well and cook 30 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars and seal, leave 1/4-inch space.

title: stained glass candy
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips over low heat. Cool slightly.
Add marshmallows (and nuts, if used).
Divide marshmallow mix in half. Spread coconut, if desired, on waxed paper. Roll each half of mixture into waxed paper.
Chill 24 hours. Slice.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, pumpkin and melted margarine.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon together.
Add to wet ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1 inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: chili soup
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a large pot and cook for at least 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put apples in 8-inch square pan. Combine the rest of the ingredients, mixing until crumbly. Sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes until apples are tender.
Serves 6.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients; boil 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour over chops.
Cover and bake in a 300° oven for 2 1/2 hours, or put in a crock-pot at low temperature all day.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Stir soup and cheese together.
Add onion, broccoli and garlic.
Place in ovenproof dish; top with more grated cheese. Bake in oven at 350° until bubbly.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, coconut, vanilla, margarine and walnuts until well blended.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into balls; chill again. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler over low heat.
With toothpicks, dip balls in chocolate mixture; return to cookie sheet and chill until set.

title: halibut fingers
directions: Cut halibut into fingers, 2 x 2 x 4-inch. Combine olive oil and garlic into a bowl. Combine the cheese and the bread crumbs. Dip the halibut into the oil mixture and then roll in the bread crumbs mixture. Place on a foil lined cookie sheet and bake in a 500° oven for 10 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Pare and slice potatoes very thinly.
Parboil in boiling salted water for 3 minutes, then drain.
Layer potatoes and onions in a 10-cup baking dish.
Sprinkle flour, salt and pepper between layers.
Pour milk over potatoes.
Dot with butter and cheese. Cover.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender and top is browned slightly. Serves 8.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Beat peanut butter and butter until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour and salt.
Spread into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top and let sit for about 5 minutes.
Morsels will be shiny and spread all over.

title: dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed on the box and spread in a lightly greased 11 x 17-inch pan.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken in 3 quarts of water until done.
Set water aside.
Take all meat off of bones.
Chop chicken up.
Put back into chicken water.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Stir altogether and pour into casserole dish.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all together and form into balls.
Place in Dutch oven. Pour tomato soup diluted over balls.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough evenly onto a lightly greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick with fork and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Cool.

title: copper pennies
directions: If whole carrots, slice in quarters in slices (these look like copper pennies).
Cook until barely tender in salt water (if one uses salt).
Drain.
Mix ingredients and pour over carrots.
Toss slightly and cover.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Serve cold as a salad or as a hot vegetable.
(I prefer cold as a salad.)

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; add taco mix and 3/4 cup water and simmer, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Put enchilada sauce in pan and heat; set aside.
Shred cheeses and set aside.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Cook and drain raisins.
Roll in flour.
Mix butter, eggs and syrup together.
Mix well and add applesauce, raisins and vanilla. Gradually stir in flour.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes in a greased loaf pan.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onion and pepper; add meat.
Add rest.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cook chicken in enough water to cover.
Cook over medium heat until chicken is tender.
Remove from broth.
Add all of the ingredients listed, except eggs.
Cook on low heat for an hour or so, until potatoes are soft.
Add chicken picked from bone.
Wait until soup is finished to add eggs.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream in very large bowl the first five ingredients. Thoroughly mix in soda, flour and salt with mixer.
Stir in all other ingredients by hand, adding cornflakes last.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add bananas and eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Put the melted butter in a bowl, adding the sugar, egg and milk.
Sift the flour and baking powder and add to the butter mixture.
Put a small amount of melted butter in bottom of a square 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle batter with brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts plus a little melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: blender mayonnaise
directions: Combine Egg Beaters, spices, sugar, vinegar and 1/2 cup oil in blender.
Cover and blend on medium to high until blended. Without turning off slowly pour in remaining 1/2 cup of oil (in a fine stream).
If necessary use a spatula to keep mixture flowing to blades.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: dressing balls with gravy
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until tender.
Mix all ingredients and form into balls.

title: rice croquettes
directions: Soften onion in the heated butter.
Add rice.
Saute until glazed.
Stir in parsley and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in egg, cheese, basil and black pepper.
Mixture should be very moist.
Shape into 12 to 16 croquettes, depending on size desired.
Roll in bread crumbs. Fry in 1/4 to 1/2-inch olive oil until golden and crisp.
Drain. Garnish with parsley when serving.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Place Cool Whip in large bowl.
Add dry jello and stir to dissolve.
Add cottage cheese, undrained pineapple and drained mandarin orange pieces. Mix well and serve. Keep refrigerated.

title: party stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown meat and cook onion in butter until tender. Stir in soup, sour cream and water.
Cover.
Simmer 45 minutes or until tender, stirring now and then.
Serve on noodles.

title: meringue tarts
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and 1 cup sugar until very stiff.
Cream butter and 3/4 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with the cream. (Use 2 round pans.)
Divide the butter mixture and spread out in pans.
Top, divided egg mixture so cake is completely covered. Bake in slow oven so meringue does not get too brown, 40 minutes. (Try sides to test doneness.)
Put fresh strawberries and whipped cream between layers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Stew and debone chicken (save the broth).
Mix soup and 2 cups broth and pour over chicken, that has been placed into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish.

title: herman's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium boiler.
Let boil for a few minutes.
It's ready to use.

title: southern banana pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir pudding mix into milk in medium saucepan.
Add yolks.
Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Arrange layer of cookies on bottom and up sides of 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add 1 layer of bananas; top with 1/3 of pudding.
Repeat layers, ending with pudding.
Beat egg whites and salt in medium bowl with electric mixer on high until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spoon onto pudding, sealing edges well.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, or until meringue is lightly browned.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and heat to boiling.
Pour over item to be barbecued.

title: hamburger upside-down pie
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and beef in oil until brown. Add tomato sauce, ketchup, chili powder, salt and pepper. Turn into a 2-quart casserole or glass pie pan. Cover meat with one of the toppings. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Turn onto a serving plate with the topping on the bottom.

title: happy valley chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: cocoa nut balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
Mix well.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut.
Place on ungreased sheet and bake 20 minutes in a 325° oven.
Cool.
Roll in confectioners sugar or frost.

title: meatball sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Makes enough sauce for about 3-4 dozen small meatballs.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Put in a 3 quart casserole.
Top with the cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This is best if put together the day before and refrigerated overnight.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat 2 egg whites as stiff as possible.
Gradually add 1/2 cup of sugar and keep beating.
Fold in one 6 ounce package of chocolate chips.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop the mix by the teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Put in oven; turn off the heat and leave for at least two hours.
Do not open oven door until time to remove.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Beat eggs; fold into cake batter with buttermilk, baking powder and vanilla.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Set aside.
Bring to a boil the canned milk and sugar. Boil for 2 minutes.
Add coconut, marshmallows and vanilla.
Beat until it begins to thicken.
Spread between layers and on top. Mix in a bowl 1/2 stick of butter, shortening, cocoa, canned milk and powdered sugar.
Spread on cake.
Very good cake.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add egg; beat well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine molasses and water; add alternately with flour mixture.
Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan with greased wax paper.
Pour batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add lemon juice and rind and egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour and milk; lastly, fold in the egg whites, beaten stiff.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Bake at 325° until set as custard.
It will require about 45 minutes.
Bottom part is custard, top like cake.

title: cheese and spinach pie
directions: Place Swiss cheese on bottom of pie crust, then spinach, mushrooms and chicken.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pizza chicken(microwave)
directions: Place chicken in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients together and generously spoon over chicken.
Microwave on High for 20 to 22 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 10 minutes.
Sprinkle cheeses over chicken and microwave 2 to 4 minutes until cheese is melted.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cube chicken.
Combine soup, sour cream and butter.
Stir in chicken, mushrooms, spaghetti and salt and pepper.
Turn mixture in a greased 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour half of batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk and butter over low heat.
Pour over cake. Sprinkle 3/4 of nuts and chocolate chips over caramel.
Pour remaining cake batter over filling and sprinkle remainder of nuts and chips on top.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple slush
directions: Mix in a large container and place in freezer.
One quart cut up strawberries may be added.
Mixture should be in freezer at least 24 hours before serving, stirring at least twice while freezing.

title: corn pudding
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, blend cornstarch and sugar.
Blend in eggs.
Add corn and milk; stir.
Add a small dash of salt, if desired; stir.
Top with pat of butter; sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
It is done when there is no liquid on top.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: pittsburgh potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
When cold, peel and shred coarsely. Shred cheese.
Heat 1/2 cup oleo and cheese until almost melted. Remove from heat; stir in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper. Fold into potatoes.
Put in 2-quart casserole; dot with 2 tablespoons oleo.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mock apple pie(no apples needed)
directions: Roll out half the pastry and line a 9-inch pie plate.
Place crackers in prepared crust.
In saucepan, over high heat, heat water, sugar and cream of tartar to a boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and rind; cool.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts, debone and chop.
Grease 9 x 13-inch dish with butter.
Drain asparagus and put in bottom of casserole. Put chicken over asparagus.
Mix soup, lemon juice and mayonnaise together and pour over chicken.
Put grated cheese over soup mixture.
Sprinkle on cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: meat sauce
directions: Brown 1 pound ground beef in oven.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook for one hour on top of stove in saucepan.
Great for spaghetti or any kind of meat.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown hamburg and onions; put in canner or large mixing bowl. Add remaining
ingredients
and
mix
well.
Use tomato juice as desired or water
may
be
added.
Pressure can at 10 pound pressure for 1 hour and
30 minutes for quart and 1 hour and 15 minutes for pints.

title: meat roast
directions: Place roast in pan.
Pour on cream of mushroom soup.
Add Lipton onion soup mix and 1/2 cup water.
Cover tightly; bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
After first hour, baste occasionally.
Slice and serve with mushroom gravy.

title: basic dough for rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water (110°).
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour; beat well.
Beat in yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour to form soft dough, beating well.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover to let it rise until double (1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: cream puffs
directions: Boil water.
Add salt, sugar, nutmeg and butter.
Stir over heat until butter has melted.
Remove from heat and immediately pour in all flour at once.
Beat vigorously with a wooden spoon until thoroughly blended.
Then beat over moderate heat for 1 or 2 minutes until mixture is smooth and forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat vigorously after each egg until mixture is smooth.
Drop batter on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; make a small slit in side of each puff.
Return to turned off oven for 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 12 puffs, about 3-inches in diameter.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cheese and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add milk and peanut butter.
Mix until creamy.
Add Cool Whip and blend well. Turn into crust and cover with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain.
Add soup and milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
While meat is simmering, prepare noodles according to package directions. Drain.
Ladle noodles onto plates.
Add meat mixture.
Cover with sour cream to taste.

title: oatmeal nut crispies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well. Add lemon extract and mix well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and pecans; shape dough into 2 long rolls, 2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper; chill 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices. Place 2 to 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Combine jello and boiling water first.
Let cool.
Line bottom of baking pan (10-inch square) with about 2 cups cracker crumbs. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy in mixing bowl.
Add well-beaten egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add cooled jello to butter mixture.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Last, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour onto cracker crumbs in pan, sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Refrigerate for 8 hours or longer.
Cut in squares and top with Cool Whip.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all together in crock-pot; cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oats, brown sugar and shortening.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Add beaten egg and the yeast dissolved in water.
Then add the salt and flour.
Mix together, then put out on counter and knead well.
It may take more flour to knead well. Place in greased bowl, turning the lump over so top will be greased.
Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Make out in loaf or rolls.
Cover and let rise again.
Bake in 325° oven for loaves or 375° for rolls.

title: ranch style stew
directions: Cook onion and pepper in shortening until tender.
Add hamburger meat and cook until it changes color.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Make crust in deep-dish or casserole dish using the dinner rolls. Layer browned sausage, hash browns and cheese. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together and pour over sausage and hash browns. Bake for 25 minutes at 375°. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese or Cheddar cheese. Bake for 5 more minutes. Serve hot or cut in squares and store in freezer bags. Reheat in microwave.

title: shoestring potatoes
directions: Layer in casserole the first 4 ingredients.
Pour the milk over and sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover the last 20 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Form balls and fry.

title: spinach casserole #2
directions: Cook spinach in a small amount of lightly salted water until thawed; drain.
Saute mushrooms in the butter for about 5 minutes.

title: oriental chicken casserole
directions: *Or use 1 cup mayonnaise and 1 cup chicken stock.

title: cap'n crunch candy
directions: Mix
all
the
ingredients.
Melt 1 package almond bark candy. Mix
and
pour
over cereal mix.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let set for 2 or 3 hours.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a baking dish. Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: praline pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare and roll out pastry.
Line a 9-inch pie plate.
Trim pastry 1/2-inch beyond edge of pie plate.
Flute edge high.
Do not prick.
Line with a double thickness of foil.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake 4 to 5 minutes more or until set and dry.
Cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll dough out on a floured surface to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutter and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until bottom of cookie is lightly browned.

title: barbara's pres. johnson chewy coconut macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat egg whites and salt until stiff. Beat in sugar until shiny peaks form.
Fold in coconut and vanilla.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Combine milk, eggs, sugar, cinnamon and salt in a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole; beat with a rotary beater.
Stir in bread cubes and raisins.
Dot with butter.
Microwave on simmer setting 26 to 28 minutes or until almost set in center.
In conventional oven, bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes or set in center. Enjoy!!!

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt soup, cheese and milk on stove.
Layer in baking dish: rice, onion, mushrooms and broccoli.
Pour mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix together and bake in a 2-quart casserole for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken mull
directions: Boil fryer.
Put broth in crock-pot.
Chop up chicken; add to broth.
Add tomatoes and corn to broth.
Simmer ingredients on low for 6 hours (this time is flexible).
About 30 minutes before serving, crumble crackers into broth and add milk.
Goes great with chicken salad sandwich and pickle!
Yummy winter dish!

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Blend cream of chicken soup and milk together.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Put crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Press a little on sides. Bake at temperature on package for 11 minutes until brown.
Cool.

title: apple pie in a paper bag
directions: Place apples in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle rest of ingredients over apples.

title: arne's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onions, garlic and green pepper.
Brown meat in separate pan.
Combine in kettle.
Add puree, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and 1 cup water.
Simmer 3 hours.
Cool overnight.
Before serving, add mushrooms and chicken.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and then add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix whipped cream and cream cheese well.
In another bowl, mix strawberries and glaze together.

title: dan's authentic polish pigs in a blanket
directions: Boil 2 quarts of water in large pot.
Slice all onions in 2 frying pans and saute in 1/4 pound of butter.
Mix all flour, eggs and water in a large bowl.
Take dough mixture and roll it into 1 large thin pizza-shaped circle.
Cut out 2 fist-size, flat pieces of dough.
Place 3 tablespoons of ground beef in the middle of the 2 pieces of dough and press ends together.
Now the pig is in the blanket.

title: apple crisp #3
directions: Line buttered 8-inch square baking pan with apple slices. Sift dry ingredients together in a bowl.
With a pastry blender, work in egg until consistency of coarse cornmeal.
Sprinkle over apples.
Drizzle with melted butter; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix orange juice and water and bring to a boil.
Add cranberry sauce and mix until smooth in a blender or with a mixer.
Place in glass bowl and put in refrigerator until starting to set.
When Jell-O starts to set, put in remaining ingredients and refrigerate until serving.

title: chocolate delight
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter.
Mix with flour and pecans. Press on bottom to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add 1/2 Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix pudding with 2 cups milk for 1 minute.
Spread over cream cheese mix.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecans.

title: pan coating
directions: Mix well.
Put in small container.
Use when baking cake in pan that has to be greased.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Dredge chops in flour, salt, pepper and ginger mixture.
Saute onions and garlic in butter.
Brown chops on each side in butter mixture.
Remove chops from pan.
Add beef broth, taco sauce, vinegar and brown sugar.
Stir.
Add chops to pan.
Cover and cook 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: cheesies
directions: Knead all ingredients together.
Make into desired shapes and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes a good snack.

title: cherry angel delight
directions: Blend sugar and cream cheese; fold in whipped topping. Tint with red food coloring, if desired. Split cake into 3 layers. Spread first layer with small amount of topping, then some of the cherry pie filling.
Repeat with second layer, reserving about 2/3 of the pie filling for garnish.
Place third layer on cake and frost cake completely with remaining topping. Carefully spoon remaining pie filling on top. Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy. Add sugar and beat until blended. Stir in oil, vanilla, zucchini and orange rind. Sift dry ingredients and stir into egg mixture along with the nuts. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat
oven
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and
beat on high speed for 5 minutes.
Fold in rest of ingredients.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Mix crumbs with 2 tablespoons butter.
Melt remaining butter with flour and seasonings.
Add sour cream and blend.
Heat until thickened.
Fold in green beans.
Pour into greased casserole (1 1/2-quart).
Top with cheese, then bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed in punch bowl.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: death by chocolate dessert
directions: Cook cake and let cool.
Make pudding as directed on box. Chop Butterfinger bars.
Layer your bowl with cake first (may be cut in squares to fit in bowl).
Then, add a layer of pudding, a layer of Cool Whip and top with candy bar, crushed.
Continue layering until all supplies are used.
Refrigerate overnight or until cool.
Enjoy!

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: For graham cracker crust, mix together graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan (for thicker crust, double recipe).

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch square pan for approximately 30 minutes.
Let cool. This shortcake will be moist.
Cut in squares and serve with strawberries or other fruits.

title: seafood casserole with macaroni
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Cook onion, green pepper and mushrooms until soft.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add cheese and lemon juice.
Heat until cheese melts.
Add mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Alternate layers of macaroni, crab, lobster and shrimp in 2 buttered casseroles.
Pour sauce over casseroles. Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Casseroles freeze well.
Yields 20 servings.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling, then pineapple in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix dry cake mix with nuts.
Spread over filling and pineapple.
Add butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: frozen punch
directions: Boil together 4 c. sugar and 6 c water until sugar is dissolved. Cool. Combine juices, lemonade and bananas with cooled sugar water. Mix well and freeze. When ready, mix with 7 Up, sour or your favorite mix to make slush consistency.

title: delicious egg custard
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Start baking at 450° for about 10 minutes.
Turn oven to 325°.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Beat 6 eggs.
Put in half and half, salt and dry mustard. Have a dripping pan and put bread cubes in bottom of pan.
Put sausage over bread, then cheese.
Last pour egg mixture over. Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Cream together margarine and brown sugar until light. Add flour and nuts. Blend until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup for topping. Press remaining dough into an 8-inch square ungreased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: frogs on a log
directions: Fill groove in celery sticks with peanut butter.
Add raisins on top.

title: savory pork chops
directions: Mix flour, seasoned salt, pepper and mustard.
Coat chops on both sides with mixture.
Heat a little oil in medium skillet with cover.
Brown chops well on both sides over medium heat.
Pour off any excess fat.
Mix water, soy sauce, ketchup and marmalade. Pour over chops.
Cover.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes or until chops are tender, turning once.
Sprinkle with chopped green onion.
Recipe may be halved or doubled.
Good served with parslied potatoes and steamed broccoli.
Preparation: 10 minutes. Cooking time: 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: "lo-cal" banana split
directions: Make Jell-O according to package directions.
Cut in cubes. Split one banana in half and place in banana split dish.
Put cubed Jell-O between both slices.
Pour whipped cream on top.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: brine for smoking fish
directions: Dissolve salt in small amount of hot water.
Add to gallon of water and rest of ingredients.
Heat to boil and let cool.
Let your fish soak overnight in brine and smoke over hickory chips or chips of your choice.

title: mint frosting
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Frost tops of 2 (8-inch) layers or tops and side of an 8-inch square cake.
Garnish with chocolate curls.

title: stove top cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter, oatmeal and nuts.
Stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: chicken and wine with mushrooms
directions: Flour, salt and pepper chicken.
Brown in butter with garlic. Sprinkle with thyme and onion tops.
Add wine to cover chicken. Simmer one hour.
During last 15 minutes, add fresh mushrooms.

title: spicy slow-cooker barbecue beef
directions: Trim any fat from meat. Season heavily on both sides with Montreal steak spice blend. Pour thin film of balsamic vinegar in slow cooker crockery pot. Put roast into pot. Pour more balsamic vinegar over meat to come up sides of meat halfway. Cover and cook on high for 1 hour. Turn roast over in pot. Re-cover and reduce heat to low. Cook on low for 8 hours. When meat is cool enough to handle, shred meat with forks or your fingers. Serve on buns with some of the sauce left in crockery pot.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican hot dogs
directions: Slice hot dogs down the middle.
Put thick piece of cheese in each hot dog.
Pre-warm tortillas over fire.
Put hot dog with cheese on each tortilla.
Roll and fry in skillet with about 4 tablespoons oil.
Fry and turn for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: pesto
directions: Put ingredients in blender; blend well.
Can add 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, also.

title: spaghetti pie(pasta main dish)
directions: In a 4 quart bowl, beat eggs, garlic powder, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Add the spaghetti and blend well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top as you would a pizza.
Put sauce over spaghetti, then cheese and pepperoni.
Return to oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
This recipe can be altered by adding sausage, mushrooms or different cheeses.

title: pickled onions
directions: Peel onions and cover with boiling water.
Drain and put into ice water to cool and crispen.
Cut red and green peppers into strips. Mix the vinegar, salt, sugar and water in saucepan.
Cook to boiling.

title: lemon pie cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, margarine and egg yolks, beating until smooth. Beat in lemon juice. Add milk slowly while stirring so it doesn't curdle. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into lemon mixture. Bake pie shell briefly (5 minutes), then pour in filling. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° until filling is firm.

title: hawkin's cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and dust a 12-inch tube cake pan.
In a large mixing bowl using a mixer, cream butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and mix at least 10 minutes.
Add extract and mix in.
Add flour alternately with eggs, beginning and ending with flour.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake for 65 to 70 minutes.

title: chicken breasts primavera
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Have a jelly roll pan ready.
Tear six 14 x 12-inch strips of foil.
Lightly coat 1 side with vegetable spray or oil.
Place chicken breast half on each piece. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Top with some of the pepper strips, green beans (or asparagus), snow peas and green onions.
Dot with margarine; sprinkle with cheese.
Fold foil and seal securely. Arrange packets on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 18 to 20 minutes until chicken is done.
Remove packets to plates.
Serve with green salad, crusty Italian bread, ice cream and peaches.
Serves 6.

title: tomato soup
directions: Empty can of tomatoes into saucepan.
Salt to taste.
Add margarine.
Heat to boiling.
Add baking powder (will foam up). Place milk into another saucepan and heat to just the boiling point.
Add milk to tomatoes.
Serve.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, and butter together until brittle when tested in cold water.
Add vinegar and remove from heat.
Have popped corn ready with all hard grains removed.
Scatter peanuts over not of popcorn if desired.

Gradually but quickly pour the syrup over the popcorn and stir briskly until corn is well coated. While still warm, form into figures with molds or form into balls. Keep in a dry, room temperature place to keep fresh and crisp.

title: tamale bake
directions: Scramble sausage in skillet; brown and drain.
Put 1 tablespoon fat in skillet.
Add onion.
Saute until tender.
Stir in sausage, beans and chili powder.
Put in a greased, shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Set aside first 2 ingredients in
bowl.
Bring
next
4 ingredients to a boil;
then pour
over
first
2 ingredients. Mix well, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix
well
and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for
hour
or
15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan and only bake 20 to 25 minutes. Ice while hot.

title: cream cheese cookie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cookie mix and butter until crumbly. Stir in nuts.
Set 1 cup aside for later use.
Press remaining mixture into an ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Bake crust until lightly browned, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans.
Form a large ball. Roll in chopped pecans until ball is covered.
Keep in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Serve with crisp crackers.

title: almond roca
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add almonds and sugar.
Increase heat to high and continue cooking, stirring continuously and rapidly until sugar melts and mixture becomes a light tan color.
Almonds may start to pop.
Remove immediately from heat.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Set aside.
Meanwhile, saute onion in butter.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in ungreased casserole uncovered for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple, then fold in Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: tomato preserves
directions: Cook tomatoes until soft.
Add sugar.
Bring to boiling point for 5 minutes.
Stir in lemon Jell-O.
Store in refrigerator.

title: micro pecan caramel ring
directions: Dot butter in the bottom of a microwave ring mold.
Add brown sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until syrup is formed.
Stir to blend.
Arrange cherry and pecan halves on syrup.
Place biscuits close together in a ring over syrup mixture.
Microwave on Medium-high for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn dish a half turn halfway through cooking.
Immediately invert onto serving plate leaving dish over cake for several minutes.
Serve warm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie(the one that makes its own crust)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in plate. Beat baking mix, milk and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and set aside.
In large bowl, add oil, salt, sugar and egg.
Cream oil and sugar; add well beaten egg, salt and yeast plus 1 cup lukewarm water.
Work in 4 cups flour.
Turn into large greased bowl; cover and put in refrigerator until needed at least overnight.
Take out; add a little more flour to pastry board and knead the dough slightly, then roll out and cut rolls out.
Let set in warm place covered about 2 hours.
Bake at 450°.
When done, brush with butter. Makes 25 to 30 rolls.

title: spinach brownies
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Run knife around edge of pan and let cool slightly.
Cut into squares.
Freezes well and can be reheated at 400° for 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: aunt mae pearl's pickled okra
directions: Divide okra into 5 pint jars (leave a short stem on okra). Put stems down in first layer and stems up in second layer. Divide dill, garlic, peppers and alum into jars.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour over okra and seal jars.
Allow okra to pickle at least 2 weeks before serving.
Yields 5 pints.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cut candy orange slices into smaller pieces.
Cream together sugars and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt and stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, candy and coconut.
Roll into tablespoon-size balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: 7 minute icing
directions: Combine in boiler and set over low flame.
Beat with electric beater while cooking until will stand in a peak.

title: quick macaroni and veggie salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
While pasta is cooking, run warm water over frozen veggies for about 3 minutes.
After draining cooked pasta, add veggies, 1 cup grated cheese and entire bottle of Italian dressing.
Mix well.
May be served immediately.
Garnish with black olives.

title: butter cake
directions: Mix together yellow cake mix, 2 eggs and 1 stick butter; spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together 8 ounces cream cheese, 2 eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread on top of first mixture. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.
When cool, sift reserved 1/4 cup sugar on top.

title: easy chicken parmesan
directions: Pound chicken until about 1/4-inch thick.
Dip in eggs and then bread crumbs.
Lightly coat frying pan with Pam oil spray or cooking oil.
Place chicken in pan and slightly brown on both sides.
Spray a shallow baking pan with Pam or cooking oil.
Spoon a thin layer of sauce on bottom of pan.
Place chicken in pan. Spoon sauce on chicken.
Place 2 slices cheese on top.
Spoon more sauce on chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cook pasta; heat remaining sauce.
Serve as a side dish with a salad. Serves 4.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture and pour in milk.
Mix to make a soft dough, then turn onto a lightly floured surface and knead briefly. Roll dough out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut biscuits, using a 2-inch floured cutter.
Arrange biscuits close together on a cookie sheet. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.
Serve warm.

title: devastating chocolate pie
directions: In top of double boiler, over boiling water, heat butter and chocolate, stirring until melted and well blended.
Allow to cool slightly.
Blend syrup, sugar, salt and vanilla into beaten eggs. Add chocolate; blend well.

title: mocha chocolate pie
directions: Combine chocolate pudding and coffee, gradually adding milk. Cook over medium heat until boiling.
Cool 5 minutes and add to baked pie shell.
When thoroughly cool, top with whipped topping.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour ingredients into pie crust and cook at 325° to 400° for 45 minutes.
This makes 1 pie.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla. Gradually pour over popped corn.
Mix well.
Turn into 2 large shallow baking or roasting pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool completely. Break apart and store in a tightly covered container.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: tangy pork chops
directions: Trim as much fat as possible from chops.
Line baking pan with foil. Beat egg, milk, lime juice, salt, pepper, oregano and garlic salt together. Dip each chop into liquid and then crumbs.
Lay on foil lined pan.
Drizzle with melted butter or margarine. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli beef
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese.
Cut up and dice onion and bell pepper. In a large skillet, cook ground beef, onion, pepper and thawed broccoli together until beef is brown and broccoli is cooked, yet still crisp.
Drain off any excess fat.
Put back in skillet and add the remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; afterwards lower heat to a good simmer.
Simmer for 10 full minutes (or until thickened somewhat).
Serve over cooked rice or pasta.
(You may substitute low-fat ground turkey for a low-fat family meal, if desired.)
Top with grated cheese on individual servings. Delicious!

title: pierogi
directions: Mix all ingredients to consistency of pie dough.
Divide into 8 pieces; roll out each shell.
Fill 1/2 of each shell with filling.
