Fold the other half over the filling, wet edge with water and seal closed.

title: oatmeal-banana cupcakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Beat in eggs, bananas and honey.
Stir in dry ingredients until blended.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips or raisins (optional).
Fill muffin pans lined with paper cups 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes. Makes approximately 24 cupcakes.

title: festive punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sherbet.
Add the sherbet on top. Serves 100.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Prepare 4 double-strength foil packets.
Oil the foil.
Place chicken on foil.
Mix undiluted soup with instant rice.
Put on top of chicken.
Seal and cook about 40 minutes, turning once or twice.

title: three week coleslaw
directions: Shred lettuce coarsely.
Slice onions; add 1 cup sugar and pour over cabbage.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour all of this over cabbage.
Keep all of this in a Tupperware container.

title: vinegar taffy
directions: Boil together until it crackles.
Pour in buttered pan to cool and until you are able to handle it.
Pull until porous. Twist and put in pan to set.
Chop in pieces.

title: fast meal
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients; add the rest of the ingredients.
(Cook the macaroni before adding.)
Cover with the cheese and bake only until the cheese melts.

title: chicken with spaghetti
directions: Simmer the chicken in water to which has been added the next 3 ingredients.
Cool in broth.
Remove skin and bone and cut meat into small pieces.

title: scalloped chicken and potatoes
directions: Combine vegetables; carefully stir in chicken.
In saucepan, combine flour, salt and dash of pepper.
Blend in milk.
Stir in catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook and stir until bubbly. Stir into vegetable mixture.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° until potatoes are tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Makes 6 servings.

title: chewy fudge squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir cake mix, eggs and butter until well blended (mixture will be stiff).
Stir in marshmallows and walnuts.
Spread into pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: quick horseradish sauce
directions: Blend all together and chill.
Serve over beef.

title: almost a julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender. Cover and blend until smooth on lowest speed of blender. Serve immediately. Makes two 8 ounce glasses.

title: strawberry glace
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in boiling water in a bowl.
Stir in the cold water and chill until slightly thickened.
Soften the cream cheese and shape into balls.
Roll in nuts.
Place alternate layers of cheese balls and strawberries in a 9-inch ring mold, covering each layer with gelatin.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and fill center with sherbet.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Add the Jiffy corn mix last. Pour into the baking pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Test, using a table knife inserted 1-inch from center.
Done when knife comes out clean.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter, oil and marshmallows.
Mix all ingredients well. Press mixture into a buttered tube pan.
Let set until cool.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine. Beat in eggs. Stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Dump flour and milk in. Beat until smooth. Put in two 9-inch greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: sweet and sour beef
directions: Brown cubes with butter in a large skillet.
Stir in flour. Combine the remaining ingredients and add to meat mixture. Simmer 20 minutes and serve over fluffy rice.

title: mom's spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in 1 tablespoon butter; drain.
Add to browned ground beef.
Add spices.
Add tomato puree and simmer over low heat one hour.
Cook and drain spaghetti. Blend meat sauce with spaghetti.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and cook until tastes blend, approximately 20 minutes.
Great the next day. Serve with Parmesan.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in 3 (9-inch)
cake
pans.
For icing, combine sugar and milk and cook over
medium heat.	Add margarine, vanilla and coconut.
Let cook until thick enough to spread on cake.

title: banana strawberry frost
directions: Combine ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Serve chilled or over ice.
Has 1 gram of fat and 112 calories per serving.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream together eggs and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Then add softened cream cheese and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat 20 minutes at medium speed in Mixmaster.
This is important.
While beating, roll 1/2 package zwieback into crumbs.
Add 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Butter bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan and dust lightly with crumbs.
Add 1/4 cup margarine to the remaining crumb mixture and moisten.
Press into bottom only to about 1/4-inch thickness. Pour cream cheese mixture into pan and bake 35 minutes, without looking!!!
This is also very important.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over medium heat in double boiler until thick.
Pour into cooled pie shell.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper in skillet.
Transfer to a slow cooking pot and add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 3 to 4 hours.

title: multi-bean soup
directions: Wash beans thoroughly and place in large bowl covered with water.
Cover and soak overnight; drain.
Place ham hocks in Dutch oven; add water, garlic, thyme and red pepper.
Bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer hocks for 1 1/2 hours.
Add beans and continue cooking for another hour.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 30 minutes more
or until beans and vegetables are done.
Yields 10 servings.

title: cavatini
directions: Warning!
This makes a big pot!
(Cut the recipe for smaller amount.)

title: stuffed cucumber cups
directions: Wash 3 small cucumbers and score lengthwise with a fork.
Cut in halves crosswise; cut off ends and hollow out centers, discarding seeds.
Save pulp.
Sprinkle insides with salt and pepper.
Chill 20 minutes. Fill cups with mixture of the cream cheese, finely chopped cucumber pulp, salt, paprika and lemon juice. Serve on beds of fresh lettuce.

title: swedish oven pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and milk. Add dry ingredients and beat well.
Pour half the batter into a hot buttered 9 x 13-inch pan or frypan. Bake until firm on top. Spread fruit, jam or jelly and cranberry sauce on pancake.
Pour rest of batter over top and bake until light brown in a 370° oven.

title: pioneer turkey casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine rice mix, turkey, celery, water chestnuts, almonds and onion.
In a small bowl, combine soup, mushrooms, water and Worcestershire sauce. Add soup mixture to rice mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover; continue baking for 20 to 30 minutes until rice is done.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: gazpacho
directions: Mix the tomatoes, cucumber, onion, green pepper, tomato juice, vinegar,
oil and garlic; add salt and pepper to taste. Puree if desired.
Chill
until cold.
Serve in small glasses or spoon into bowls.

title: home made bread
directions: Heat sugar, shortening, salt and 1 1/2 cups of water in sauce pan until melted.
Add 2 cups cold water and let cool.

title: dump cake
directions: In a greased, 9 x 13-inch baking dish, spread layers of pineapple, pie filling and dry cake mix.
Do not mix layers. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Top with thin pats of butter and chopped nuts.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: nine layer dip
directions: Layer a large casserole dish with ingredients in order, beginning with the chicken.
Cook at 350° until thoroughly warm.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop first 5 ingredients very fine.
Add sugar, salt and vinegar.
Add enough water to mixture to make 5 gallons of chow chow.
Cook only until hot; place in jars.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine in microwave.
Pour over Rice Chex to coat.
Put 10x sugar in a paper bag.
Pour in coated Rice Chex.
Store in airtight container for a good snack.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
In another large bowl, mix sugar and shortening until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Pour flour mixture (slowly) into sugar mixture.
Add water as needed. Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: ravine brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Cool thoroughly.
Add sugar, eggs, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Beat well.
Spread evenly in greased pan (9 x 7-inches).
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until done.
Test with toothpick.
If tester comes out sticky, not doughy, brownies are done.
They will be soft and chewy.

title: brown sugar glaze for ham
directions: Add enough orange and/or pineapple juice to make it thin enough to spread on ham.

title: presto dip
directions: Mix well. Cover. Chill.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine according to directions; drain.
Add Salad Supreme and Italian dressing.
Marinate overnight.
Next day, chop all vegetables and add to mixture.
Mix real good.
Enjoy.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine cake mix and pudding mix.
Add eggs, oil, orange juice, Galliano and vodka.
Beat on low speed for 1/2 minute, then on medium speed for 5 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan (Bundt).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Or, pour into two 9-inch greased and floured pans and bake only 30 minutes. Cool in pans for 10 minutes; remove to rack; pour glaze on cake while it's still warm.

title: oven eggs
directions: Cube bread and spread in a 2-quart greased casserole.
In a heavy saucepan, melt cheese and butter.
Pour over bread.

title: lemon barbecue chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar, except chicken.
Shake well to blend.
Pour over chicken.
Cover tightly and marinate in refrigerator 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
(I have done it for 4 hours; it is okay.)
Cook on grill 20 to 25 minutes, brushing often with marinade.
Turn and cook 20 minutes.

title: crab broccoli casserole
directions: *May use scallops and imitation crab.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop chipped beef and onion.
Mix ingredients; shape into ball.
Sprinkle with paprika and chives.
Chill overnight.

title: white chocolate macadamia nut cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, confectioners sugar and flour to form dough.
Press evenly into 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: honey moist cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, stir together flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Pour into greased 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, or until pick comes out clean. Serves 6.

title: chicken, sausage and red potatoes
directions: Heat oil and brown sausage and thighs on all sides. Remove meat. Add water and scrape to dislodge brown bits from bottom of pan and return meat, onions, peppers and potatoes. Cook, covered, over low heat until thighs and potatoes are tender, 35 to 40 minutes. Stir occasionally.
When tender, cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, over medium heat until liquid has evaporated and meat and potatoes are browned.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: jack's crunchy crispy cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg, melted shortening or oil and mix well.
Pour into well-greased 6-inch square pan and bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield: 9 (2-inch) cornbread squares.

title: winter carrots
directions: You will need peat moss and 1 box.

title: cherry delight
directions: In a large, flat Pyrex dish, spread pie filling.
Beat together cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar and vanilla.
Spread evenly on top of pie filling.

title: taquitos
directions: Make from shredded meat (roast).
Heat each corn tortillas; keep them warm in a dish towel.
Then fill each tortilla with meat; roll each.
Fry in hot oil.
Drain on a paper towel.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, put cut rhubarb, sugar and marshmallows with the jello sprinkled on top.
Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Pour over other ingredients in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes or so and invert out of pan.
Serve.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables in salted water.
Drain.
Blend and cook the next 4 ingredients until smooth.
Add Cheddar cheese, pimentos and chopped green onion tops.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli.
Heat butter and onion in saucepan.
Put broccoli in casserole bowl.
Take butter and onion and pour in broccoli.
Put cheese on broccoli, then crumble Ritz crackers on top of cheese. Put in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable burger soup
directions: Brown meat and drain. Stir in rest of ingredients, cover and simmer.
Works good in slow cooker.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: holiday nuggets
directions: Mix all and shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: jellied persimmon salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add rest of ingredients. Chill.

title: creamy lemon cheese cake
directions: Measure 1 cup dry cake mix and set aside.
Combine remaining mix with egg and oil.
Press in the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine reserved mix, 2 eggs and remaining ingredients.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes.
Spread over baked crust; bake at 350° for about 35 minutes and cool.

title: quick beef soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in Dutch oven until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in water, sauce mix, bay leaf, salt, pepper and tomatoes; break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally; stir in noodles and vegetables.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer; remove bay leaf.
Serve with hard rolls or breadsticks if desired.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: cheater soup
directions: Cook sausage first until done, then add all other ingredients until done.
Add dash of garlic salt to taste.

title: almond joys
directions: Heat syrup.
Add coconut.
Let set 1 hour.
Shape into mounds. Place toothpick in each.
Chill 1 hour.

title: santa's red raspberry ring
directions: Drain raspberries, reserving syrup.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring until melted. Stir in lemonade concentrate and reserved syrup.
Chill until partially set.
Add raspberries and pecans.
Turn into a 6-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salt water for 6 minutes, then drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix broccoli, onion and butter. Add soup, rice and Cheez Whiz.
Bake in greased casserole for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage spread
directions: Mix together cabbage, apricots and walnuts.
Moisten with mayonnaise.
Spread between slices of hearty whole wheat bread.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a 9-inch nonstick skillet, melt margarine. Add vegetables and saute over medium heat until carrots are tender-crisp, 2 to 3 minutes. Add chicken and stir to combine. Sprinkle flour over vegetables and chicken mixture. Stir quickly to combine. Cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute. Continue to stir.
Gradually add broth; bring mixture to a boil. Reduce heat to low and let simmer until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: elsie's swiss steak
directions: Pierce steak with fork or pound with meat hammer.
Use soft butter on both sides and cover meat thoroughly.
Roll steak in flour.
Spread onions about 1 inch thick on top.
Place in a large pan with cover (or use foil).
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 325°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook, debone and cut chicken into bite-size chunks.
Grease large casserole and line with cooked cut-up chicken.
Mix soup, sour cream, melted butter and mayonnaise.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Crush crackers; add poppy seed and almonds.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fluffy pancakes
directions: Add egg whites last.

title: chicken, shrimp and scallops provencal(serves 6)
directions: In a good, fruity olive oil, saute the shrimp and scallops over moderate heat, until shrimp are pink and scallops are firm. Remove with slotted spoon and set aside.
Add chicken to pan; saute until just cooked.
Remove and set aside.

title: chinese casserole with hamburger
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients together.
Drain and add other ingredients except noodles.
Put in casserole dish and top with noodles; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stressless coleslaw
directions: In very large bowl, combine cabbage, carrots, green pepper and salt.
Cover and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Drain well.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Grind potato and onion together.
Add and mix together hamburg, ground pork, egg, allspice, salt and pepper.
Form into small balls and fry in oil until cooked through.
Remove meatballs from pan.
For gravy, add 2 tablespoons flour to oil and bring to boil.
Add 1 cup water and cook until thick.
(Adjust water for proper thickness.)
Add meatballs to gravy.

title: unbaked oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir well.
Put in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Take off burner and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper, then chill.

title: herb potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes lengthwise.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle lightly with basil, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until tender and brown.

title: recipe for friendship
directions: Sprinkle generosity with kindness and plenty of faith.
Mix well and spread over a period of a lifetime.
Serve everyone you meet.

title: swiss bliss
directions: Put the round steak in a pan.
Pour the mushrooms and tomatoes over the steak.
Slice the onion and green pepper over the steak. Place in the oven.
Cook at 350° for about an hour.
Serve 5 or 6 people.

title: quaker choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.

title: walnut salad
directions: Put 1/2 cup cold water into a small bowl.
Sprinkle two envelopes of unflavored gelatin on water.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes to soften.
Heat 2 cups apple cider until very hot; add salt.
Remove from heat and immediately add softened gelatin.
Stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Have a 1-quart mold lightly greased with cooking oil.
Do not use olive oil.
Spoon about 1/2 cup of gelatin mixture into mold and place in refrigerator.
Chill remaining mixture until slightly thickened.
Dice apples and chop walnuts and parsley.
Add this to the gelatin and place into the mold which already has thin bottom layer of gelatin.
Chill until set.
Unmold onto serving plate which has been decorated with lettuce leaves.
Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 40.7 g, protein 2.6 g, fat .9 g, calories 174.6.

title: lemon rice
directions: Grate peel and squeeze juice from lemon.
In 2-quart saucepan over high heat, heat lemon juice, salt, turmeric and water to boiling.
Stir in rice; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
When rice is done, stir in grated lemon peel.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients together.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Bake in tube pan for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs several minutes.
Add sugar.
Sift flour 4 times. Add baking powder and salt with last sift.
Add vanilla.
Fold in hot milk.
Mix into batter.
Bake in a cold oven, then at 350° until done.

title: lemon-blueberry brunch cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the cake mix, 1/4 cup margarine and cream cheese.
Mix with an electric mixer at low speed until fine crumbs form.
Set aside 1 cup of the crumbs.
Add the water and eggs to the remaining crumb mixture and beat for 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Spoon the pie filling over the batter gently spreading to cover.
Combine reserved crumbs with almonds and sprinkle over the pie filling. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until set in the center and edges are golden brown.
Cool for 25 minutes.
Mix confectioners sugar,
1 tablespoon margarine, milk and lemon extract until glaze is smooth.
Drizzle over warm cake.

title: night before casserole
directions: *Or use two cans of the same soup.

title: deme's raisin jumbo cookies
directions: This recipe I began making while I was just 12 years old.
It is a favorite in our home, and I hope in yours, too!

title: tom's catfish court bouillon
directions: In a Dutch oven, make a roux with flour and margarine; cut off fire and add onions, bell pepper, celery and garlic, stirring mixture until it stops sizzling.
Add tomato sauce and paste. Heat and stir over low heat for a few minutes.
Add 2 quarts of water; stir well and bring to boil.
Add Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Lower heat; cover and let simmer at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking on bottom.

title: terry's "dilly" of a pea soup
directions: Bring 4 quarts of water to a boil.
Add the 2 onions and the bones.
Cook until tender.
Remove meat from bones and return to pot.
Discard the bones.
Skim the fat.
Add carrots, soup mix, dill and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook about 45 minutes.
Add one can undiluted Campbell's pea soup.
Heat through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
May substitute peaches, melon or grapes for fruit choices.

title: ornament dough
directions: Combine the ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it becomes the consistency of biscuit dough.
Turn out onto board or counter.
Place in airtight bag.
This dough will keep for several weeks in the refrigerator. It is a pliable white dough.
It's great for school projects, maps, statues, ornaments, etc.

title: stella d'oro dessert cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Cut cookies in half. Fill each with mixture.
Replace top.

title: chicken delight
directions: Boil chicken until it turns white.
While chicken is cooking, mix rice, water, butter, vegetables and mushrooms in a casserole dish.
Mix in chopped chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: basic marinara sauce
directions: In large pan, saute oil, garlic and onion.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
At the end, add basil (fresh if possible) and hot pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over pasta!

title: chilly dillies
directions: Drain and rinse pickles. Add pickle spices and 1/2 sugar. Then, each day for 4 days, add 1/4 cup sugar. Keep refrigerated. Eat on the 6th day.

title: popovers
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Have muffin pan greased and hot.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 5 to 10 minutes until done.

title: filled whole wheat cookies
directions: Mix soft butter with honey.
Add flour; stir until soft dough forms.
Roll into tablespoon size balls.
Dip in egg white, then roll in nuts.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Make indentation in center, pressing nearly through.
Bake at 300° for 5 minutes, then at 350° for 15 minutes.
Five minutes before finished, fill each center with preserves.

title: skillet delight
directions: Brown meat in a large iron skillet.
Pour off fat.
Add chopped onion, pepper, okra and tomatoes.
Salt to taste.
Add about 1/2 teaspoon sugar. Simmer until almost done.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Place
margarine in baking dish and melt in oven.
Heat fruit, sugar
and	water
in
saucepan until the sugar is dissolved. Bring
to
a
boil.
Mix
flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and milk together in mixing bowl and stir until smooth. Remove	baking dish
from oven when the margarine has melted. Add flour mixture, then fruit mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375°. Crust will rise to the top and brown.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Combine 1st 4 ingredients.
Boil until bubbly.
Add cream and cook for 1 minute more.
Add vanilla.
Thin with milk or cream if too heavy when cold.

title: strawberry delight salad
directions: Just pour everything in the bowl and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Then refrigerate for about an hour or freeze, depending on which firmness you prefer.

title: cowboy stew
directions: While browning meat, add onion to cook; drain.
If carrots and potatoes aren't cooked, put them in a pot and cover with water; cook until tender.
Drain.
Add all cooked ingredients with remaining ingredients; simmer 1 hour.

title: graham cracker fluff
directions: Crush graham crackers and add sugar and melted butter.
Press graham cracker mixture into bottom of bowl. Set aside.
In a large bowl, soak gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water. Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and milk. Cook until slightly thickened.
Pour hot mixture over softened gelatin and stir until smooth.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add to chilled mixture, also add vanilla and whipped cream.
Pour mixture over graham cracker crust.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: chocolate crinkles cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl with electric mixer until fluffy.
Beat in eggs. Beat in vanilla and chocolate until blended.
Beat in flour mixture on low speed until blended.
Refrigerate dough 1 hour or until firm.
Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease sheets.
Shape heaping teaspoonfuls of dough into 1-inch balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on cookie sheets. Bake 12 minutes until tops are puffed and cracked.
Do not overbake.

title: butter balls
directions: Blend all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Roll in balls and bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Take them out of the oven and roll them hot in powdered sugar.

title: light fish chowder
directions: Cook vegetables until tender in water.
Stir in fish and milk; cook until fish is opaque.
Add flour for thickening at last.

title: chewy peanut brownie bars
directions: Combine ingredients and spread in the bottom of an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together except 1/4 cup of melted margarine. Use that to make bread crumbs for top.
Combine the margarine and kind of judge how much bread crumbs to use for topping on the casserole.
Put into well-greased dish, about 13 x 9-inch.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: easter eggs - coconut cream
directions: In a large bowl cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and condensed milk.
Beat until blended.
Add sugar, 2 cups at a time, blending well after each addition.
Add coconut and use your hands to blend.
Shape into eggs.
Dip in melted chocolate and allow to harden.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt margarine in small pan.
Mix flour in and add milk.
Cook until thickened.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning mix with mixer.
Refrigerate after spreading mixture over pizza pan or tray.
Before serving, cover with shredded lettuce, cheese and diced tomatoes.
Serve with plain tortilla chips.
Scoop dip from tray with chips.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach to remove liquid.
Mix spinach, onion and sour cream.
Add mayonnaise and seasonings.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Cut off top of bread.
Scoop out inside of loaf, retaining pieces of bread to use as dipper.
Arrange pieces around the loaf filled with the dip and serve.

title: cabbage salad mold
directions: Prepare jello as directed on box, adding 1/2 cup less water. Stir in salad dressing.
When cool and almost set, stir in rest of ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: sugar-free raisin bars
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, cook raisins, water, margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg until margarine is melted.
Continue cooking for 3 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Spread into an 8-inch square baking pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Yield: 16 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: stack pudding
directions: 1st layer: Mix butter, flour and nuts together. Press in baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stir-fry chicken in pitas
directions: Cut chicken into 1/8-inch slices. Cut each slice crosswise into matchstick thin strips. Combine chicken and next 6 ingredients. Set aside. Core cabbage and thinly slice to make about 5 cups.
Cut green onions crosswise into 3-inch long pieces. Cut carrots into matchstick thin strips.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine cake mix and pudding together.
Add oil and eggs; mix. Add 7-Up last.
Cook in 4 layers at 300°.

title: company potato dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups crushed corn flakes. Melt 1/4 cup
butter and drizzle on top of corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time. Add flavoring. Mix 1/2 cup flour with nuts and set aside. Add remaining sifted flour with baking powder.
Mix a little cream and a little flour until well blended. Fold in nuts. Bake in tube pan, greased and floured,
at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or tube pan. Preheat oven to 325°.

title: * potluck beans *
directions: In large saucepan, combine baked beans, green beans, undrained lima beans and instant minced onion.
Stir in smoked sausage pieces.
Cook over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture is heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water and oats; let stand 20 minutes.
Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
While still warm, put topping on cake and return to oven to broil for 5 minutes.

title: lemon drops
directions: Mix; shape into balls.
Drop into powdered sugar to cover. Bake on aluminum foil at 350° for 10 minutes.
Can be baked on ungreased tins, if desired.

title: quick root beer
directions: Mix in gallon jug and let set in warm place for approximately 1 day.
Then refrigerate and serve.
Will taste similar to pop.

title: miracle cheesecake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool until almost set. Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in gelatin.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped evaporated milk into gelatin mixture.
Add lemon juice.
Crush graham crackers into fine crumbs and add melted butter or margarine.
Firmly pack 2/3 of crumb mixture in bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add filling and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill several hours.
Cut in squares and serve. (This can be made in advance and frozen.
Thaw slightly before serving.)

title: smoked tuna dip
directions: Mix and cover.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Melt bouillon cubes in hot water; set aside.
Brown pork chops on both sides.
Grease casserole well.
Place 1 tablespoon rice for each chop in bottom of casserole.
Place chops on top of rice. Place 1 slice of each: green pepper, onion and tomato on top of each chop.
Cover with chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chops are done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple cheese spread
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.

title: cindy's hash brown potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients (except cheese).
Smooth out into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven and melt cheese.
Fills 7 x 11-inch pan.

title: paul's pasta salad
directions: Toss macaroni, tomatoes, onions, olives and pepperoni together.
Just before serving, toss again with a small amount of olive oil and with red wine vinegar to taste.
Top with cheese. Heat in microwave and serve.

title: lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake 30 minutes.
Cool and chill.
Top with whipped cream and garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in oven at 475° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.
This makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: Up to 1 hour before serving, combine cole slaw mix, green onions, Ramen noodles (save the seasoning mix packet for the dressing), almonds and sunflower kernels in a salad bowl.
Cover and chill.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry quick bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and cut in the margarine with pastry blender.
Combine, then add all at once the eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir until flour is just moistened.
Mixture should be lumpy.
Add berries and nuts.
Mix well.

title: moose meatballs
directions: In a bowl, combine meat, egg, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
In a large skillet, brown meatballs in oil.
Cover and cook over low heat until done.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, garlic, onion and oregano.
Drain and add tomato sauce.
Allow to simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles (with oil to prevent sticking) and allow to soak in cold water.
Cook spinach and drain.

title: pasta-crab salad
directions: Break vermicelli into 2 inch lengths.
Cook according to directions.
Rinse with cold running water and drain well.
In a medium bowl, toss vermicelli with remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill 20 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: shipwreck
directions: Layer in slow cooker, ground beef, potatoes, onion, beans and cheese. Pour soup over top. Season with salt and pepper. Dot with butter. Cover and cook on low 6-8 hours. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese if desired.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening together until crumbly.
Beat egg; add vinegar and ice water and mix together.
Add to flour mixture; mix well and form into ball.
Roll between sheets of wax paper.
Makes 3 pie crusts or put in plastic bag and refrigerate. Will keep 1 week.

title: shirley's pecan pralines
directions: Cook until soft ball stage.
Add pecans.
Cook again until soft ball stage.
Remove from fire and beat until candy thickens. Spoon onto freezer or waxed paper.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Put chips on bottom of bowl or pan.
Put boiled chicken on top of chips.
Mix soup and tomatoes; pour over chicken.
Pour milk on top of all of it.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Put in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until bubbly or cheese is melted and browned a little.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Combine all vegetables. Pour sauce over mixture and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: pan-fried eggplant
directions: Pare eggplant; cut in half lengthwise, then cut crosswise, making 1/2-inch thick slices.
Combine egg and water.
Dip eggplant in egg mixture, then in mixture of bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Cook eggplant in hot oil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lamb balls
directions: Mix the first seven ingredients together and make small balls. Roll in cracker crumbs.
Combine milk and brown sugar; pour over meatballs.
Add sherry until almost covered.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can make and refrigerate the day before.

title: alma's pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well in order listed: margarine, Crisco, sugar, eggs, flour, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Bake at 275° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry sherbet
directions: Mix together and pour into ice cream freezer.
Fill remainder of can with fresh milk.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: cheese filled monkey bread
directions: Cut bread dough into 32 pieces.
Place 1 cheese cube in center of each dough piece, shaping a ball around each piece.
Pinch dough to seal. Dip dough balls into butter.
Layer dough balls, seam side up, into a greased Bundt pan.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, for 30 to 40 minutes. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Invert onto platter. Serve warm.

title: chop suey
directions: Saute onions and celery in large frypan or wok in oil.
Add 1 cup water and salt.
Cover and boil for 4 minutes.
Mix together the sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce and 4 tablespoons water.
Add to mixture in pan with bean sprouts.
Add pork or chicken and simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve with chow mein noodles.

title: kota riganati b(chicken oregano)
directions: Combine the olive oil, 2 teaspoons of the salt and the lemon juice; rub on chicken, inside and out.
Place the chicken in a roasting pan.
Roast in a 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: grandma's bible cake
directions: Follow the directions of Solomon for bringing up a child, Proverbs 23:14.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: green onion-potato soup
directions: In large saucepan cover diced potatoes and green onions with water.
Cook until tender.
Turn heat down low.
Add half and half and butter.
Add instant potatoes to thicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook just until thoroughly heated.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into small pieces.
Cover with sauce and honey. Cook in microwave for 9 minutes.

title: play it again pasta - great soup(day 2)
directions: Mix well and heat.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine and toss with Italian dressing. Chill before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: lima mushroom casserole
directions: Cook lima beans as directed. Drain and blend in soup and pimentos.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour melted oleo over mixture and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: meatless loaf
directions: Butter a baking dish. Layer 1/2 of the bread crumbs and then layer 1/2 of the carrots, celery, peas and potatoes. Add all the onions. Sprinkle with 1/2 of the salt. Place another layer of the vegetables and sprinkle the rest of the salt on top. Beat eggs well and pour over top of vegetables. Cover with remaining buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: toll house squares
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold into sugar mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and chips.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan (mixture is stiff).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: curried couscous salad
directions: Cook chicken; cool and dice.
Cook couscous and cool.
Combine chicken, couscous, carrots, peas, red peppers and green onions. After soaking raisins in orange juice, drain and add raisins to couscous, reserving orange juice.
Combine vinegar, orange juice, curry, mustard, salt and pepper.
Shake or blend thoroughly.
Add oil and blend.
Pour over couscous and toss.
Chill until serving.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
Grease 1 6-cup loaf pan, 9 1/4 X 5 1/4 X 2 1/2 inch, with butter.

In a large saucepan, over medium heat, add the half and half. When the cream comes to a gentle boil, whisk in 1 cup of the chocolate chips, whisking constantly until all the chips have melted and are incorporated into the cream, remove from heat.
Whisk the eggs, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, vanilla and Grand Marnier together, in a large mixing bowl until very smooth.
Add the egg mixture to the cream mixture and mix well.
Add the bread, incorporate thoroughly and let the mixture sit for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour half of the mixture into the prepared pan.
Sprinkle the top with the remaining chocolate chips.
Pour the remaining bread mixture over the chocolate chips.
Bake until the pudding is set in the center, about 55 minutes.
Let cool for 5 minutes.
To serve, cut the pudding into 1 inch thick slices.
Top with spiced cream, the recipe of which follows.
Makes 10 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook sliced carrots in salt water until tender.
Do not overcook.
Alternate layers of carrots, onion and pepper in glass bowl.
Mix all other ingredients and beat 3 minutes.
Pour over carrots; sprinkle with paprika.
Chill 24 hours.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix chicken mixture.
If too dry, add chicken broth.

title: potatoes and chives, oven-browned
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut each potato into 4 wedges, then cut wedges in half.
Rinse with cold water.
Place potatoes in a large pot with water just over the top of potatoes. Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down to medium-high and cook for 20 minutes or until potatoes can be easily cut with a fork.
Drain.

title: souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a casserole dish, sprayed with cooking oil.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until center is set.

title: oven baked potato wedges(microwave recipe for 2 "oldies")
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise to wedges and leave rind on.
Put potatoes in microwave-safe dish; add onions.
Sparsely add salt; brush on both margarine and browning spray.
Microwave about 8 1/2 minutes on High.
(If you do it right, you'll go back and make a second batch before you finish eating.)

title: chocolate icing
directions: Cream the butter. Sift into it the powdered sugar and cocoa. Use just enough cream to make good spreading consistency.

title: fresh apple bake
directions: Beat sugar and oil together; sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture, alternating with eggs, beating after each addition. Add vanilla and fold in nuts and apples; pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Batter will be thick.

title: ugly cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over cake.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown or approximately 35 minutes.

title: cream cheese rolls
directions: Mix all and spread on the tortillas, roll up, let stay in refrigerator until well chilled.
Cut into little rolls.
No cooking.

title: cajun rice
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in oil until tender.
Add rice; cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven in shallow pan.
Cover; bake for 1 1/2 hours, or until rice is tender.

title: rolos-filled cookies
directions: Combine the flour, cocoa and baking soda; set aside.
Cream the sugars and margarine.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix flour into creamed mixture.
Chill dough.
With floured hands, shape 1 tablespoon of dough around a Rolos.
Cover completely.
Roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased sheet 7 to 10 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on pan, then cool on rack.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Use a bit of cake mix with flour.)
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in pan over low heat, stirring constantly.
When melted, cover and set aside to cool.
Combine cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk, margarine and nuts.
Spread 1/2 of cake mixture in cake pan and bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread warm caramel mixture over chips.
Crumble rest of cake mixture over caramels and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool before cutting.

title: ma's rice pudding
directions: Put rice in top of double boiler (2-quart). Put water in, leaving 1-inch space to top of pan.
Cook over boiling water for 1 hour.
Water will be absorbed.
Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and spices.
Add this and raisins to rice.
Cook 15 more minutes over boiling water.

title: freckle bread
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into lightly greased loaf pans (3).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top will crack.

title: texas favorite dip
directions: Brown the hamburger meat and add the rest of the ingredients.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Set aside seasoned (salted and peppered) crawfish tails. Saute onions, celery, green onions and mushrooms in butter until soft and clear in color.
Add soups and stir until smooth.
Add crawfish and simmer for 25 minutes.
During last 5 minutes, stir in parsley.
Serve over rice.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine; add to the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: gratin dauphinois(potatoes "au gratin")
directions: My father was Puerto Rican and Cuban.
My mother is German and Irish.
When they got married, my mother got my Cuban grandmother's recipe for Spanish rice.
Being a picky eater herself and having 4 kids, my mom distilled the recipe down to a mild version without all the "slimy" things in it that most kids won't eat.
I jokingly call it my mother's Irish Spanish rice!
Each year on Three King's Day (January 6), I bring this rice in for my children's classes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook and drain noodles. Cook beef and sausage. Drain. Add next 7 ingredients.
Simmer uncovered for 1 hour.

title: meatballs and rice
directions: Mix soup mix and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Put 2 tablespoons tomato sauce into cup.
Add seasoning and mix well.
Add mixture to ground beef and blend well.
Add remaining sauce to onion soup mixture.
Shape into small balls and place in casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over meatballs.
Cook one hour at 350°.
Serve over plain or spiced rice.
Makes 20 meatballs.

title: hamburger tater tot casserole
directions: Mix together the beef, onion, salt and pepper; put in baking dish.
Combine mushroom soup, water and sour cream; pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, or at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into muffin pans.	Bake at 400° until brown.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet and saute onions in same.
In a large mixer bowl combine eggs, Bisquick, cottage cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Beat on medium until very well mixed.
Add onions and beat until well blended.
Pam mini-muffin tins.
Fill about 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Press 1/2-inch thick into baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chip and dip
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage.
Add the rest of it.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream all ingredients, but shrimp.
Add to taste garlic salt, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Add shrimp.

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add cream and stir well.
Pour into an unbaked shell.
Dot with bits of butter and a little nutmeg.
Bake in a moderate oven until filling is thick.
Stir with a fork several times while the pie is baking to prevent settling.

title: maw maw rice's cocoa pies(makes 3 pies)
directions: Cook until thick and pour into baked pie crust.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Cook mixture slowly until tender and slightly thickened.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Pour into jar and seal.

title: mandel bread
directions: Mix above ingredients all together.
Grease a cookie sheet and form dough into 3 to 4 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven.

title: marinated steak
directions: Mix together the wine, soy sauce and seasonings.
Place the steak in a long
glass
baking
dish and pour the marinade over the meat.
Cover and
chill
at
least
to
18 hours, turning meat once or twice.

title: prairie hot dish
directions: Brown meat and onion in shortening.
Mix in the salt, pepper, corn, soup, water and cheese.
Pour into a 2-quart shallow casserole.
Top with the chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chilled kona cucumber soup
directions: Cook the potatoes in the stock and white wine until soft, then add all of the other ingredients, except the heavy cream.
Simmer 5 minutes. Cool.
Process the soup in a food processor or blender until smooth. Chill well. When ready to serve, add the cream. Serve the soup in chilled glass bowls for a cool look.
Garnish with a sprig of fresh mint, if desired.

title: goat meat stew
directions: Steam meat until well done; set aside.
In a saucepan heat oil until hot.
Saute onion.
Add meat to oil.
Fry meat for 1 minute and add tomato paste.
Stir in blended fresh tomato and bell pepper.
Add all other seasoning ingredients.
Let stew simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over white rice, boiled potatoes or eat with any other food of your choice.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Peel and slice eggplant 1/4-inch thick.
Beat eggs with water.
Heat oil to 350°.
First dip eggplant slices in flour, then egg, then crumbs.
Fry on both sides until golden; drain well on brown paper bag or paper towels.
Arrange in casserole dish, layering eggplant, cheese and sauce.
You may add browned hamburger, Italian sausage, whatever you prefer to the sauce or as a separate layer.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and sauce is bubbly.
Serve with a green salad and garlic bread.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers; clean and soak for 5 minutes in hot water.
Mix first 5 ingredients and put into peppers.
Place peppers in greased baking dish and pour tomato soup over the top. Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: super duper rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Stir in next 5 ingredients until dissolved, then cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and 2 cups flour.
When smooth, add 6 to 7 cups flour.
Knead until smooth. Let raise until double.
Shape in rolls and raise again.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: In a bowl, arrange the sliced cucumbers, salting them in layers.
Cover with a saucer and weight down with something heavy. Let stand for several hours, or until juices run out.
Pour off the cucumber juice, which will take care of most of the salt. Combine all other ingredients and add to the cucumbers.
Mix and chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: seasoned cornbread
directions: Combine muffin mix and poultry seasoning; add egg and milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into a well-greased 8-inch square baking dish; bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Combine cherry pie filling and lemon juice. Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole. Combine flour, brown sugar and cinnamon. Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly. Stir in oats. Sprinkle mixture over pie filling. Bake at 425° for 20 to 24 minutes. Serve with ice cream, if desired. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: goulash
directions: Saute onion, carrots and garlic in oil for 5 minutes.
Add meat and m.s.g. and brown 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 2 hours.
Serve on broad, hot, buttered noodles.

title: gyoza
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.

Take small amounts of meat mixture (about 1 tablespoon) and place in center of wonton wrap. With wet fingers, wet all sides of wonton wrap and fold over into a triangle, pressing all sides down firmly, flattening the meat mixture lightly.

title: spinach salad
directions: Rinse spinach and drain well to remove excess water.
Remove large stems and tear spinach into bite size pieces.
Arrange spinach in salad bowl.

title: hamburger hobos
directions: Make hamburger into a 4-inch patty for each person.
On each patty place sliced potatoes, onion or cheese.
Dab of butter on top; wrap in foil tent style.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Pour dressing over warm spaghetti.
Add green onions, bell peppers, black olives and cheese.
Put in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: italian beef rice skillet
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Drain mushrooms and tomatoes, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to make 2 cups of liquid.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes, liquid, rice and sauce mix to meat.
Stir. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and cook on low heat for 25 minutes or until rice is tender and mixture right consistency. Stir occasionally.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: seaside apple dumplings(the old-fashioned kind)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles meal, then stir in milk until you have a soft dough.
Roll out into a large rectangle on a floured board and cut into 6 squares.
Place an apple on each square, moisten the edges and fold to enclose fruit, pinching seams securely.
Set dumplings in shallow baking dish.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in large casserole (2-quart).
Top generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage and cheese toast
directions: Brown sausage and drain off fat.
Mix sausage and Cheez Whiz. Cut open English muffins.
Top each half with sausage and cheese mixture.
When ready to serve, toast for a few minutes in oven. These can be prepared ahead of time and kept in refrigerator or freezer.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream
Crisco,
sugar
and
eggs.
Add
vanilla.
Sift together
the flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar and add to the wet mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Chill dough.
Shape into balls. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Crush crackers with rolling pin.
Mix crackers and soft butter with a fork.
Cook broccoli halfway.
Drain.
Sprinkle cracker mixture on bottom of a square 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish or an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Save reserve for top.
Add and layer broccoli in pan or dish.
Top broccoli with favorite cheese.
Sprinkle rest of cracker mixture over top.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and cracker mixture is a light brown.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar in bowl.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk to the cream mixture.
Strain cherries; add water to the juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Add extract. Mix cornstarch with remaining sugar; add to liquid.
Add food coloring.
Pour hot juice over batter. Spread cherries over top.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Great with chips or raw vegetables.

title: butter nut balls
directions: Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Gradually add flour, salt then nuts.
Form balls size of walnuts.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 15 minutes or until slightly brown.
Roll in powdered sugar when slightly cool.

title: barbecued baked beans
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
In a heavy skillet, saute the bacon strips over medium heat until crisp.
Add the onion and garlic and continue cooking until the onion is transparent, but not browned. Transfer the bacon, onion and any fat that may have accumulated to a mixing bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients and combine well. Pour the mixture into an ungreased 2-quart baking dish and bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serves 4.

title: cod fillet
directions: Thaw cod fillets.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare large baking pan with vegetable pan coating spray.
Sort cut fish into six equal serving pieces.
Place in prepared pan.
Combine remaining ingredients except lemon wedges.
Mix well.
Spread on top of fish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
One 4-ounce serving contains 185 calories.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry; add wet.
Mix well.
Pour in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes; cool.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and egg; add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Form into small balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: brandied peaches
directions: Sprinkle with light brown sugar.
Add 2 Tbsp. brandy.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Spread batter evenly in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with nuts.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel sprinkled with sifted confectioners sugar and starting at narrow end, roll cake and towel together; cool on rack.
Unroll; spread with filling.
Roll up again.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In saucepan, boil potatoes in jackets until tender. Drain, peel and mash.
Measure out 4 cups sweet potatoes in large mixing bowl and blend in sugar, butter and spices.
Stir in egg mixture until thoroughly blended.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake on lowest rack in a 325° oven for 40 minutes or until light brown.

title: cheese stuffed loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut bread lengthwise.
Mix butter, thyme and Tabasco; spread on both sides of bread.
Layer onions then top with cheese.
Put top back on bread, wrap in foil and bake 20 to 25 minutes until crusty.

title: hot hamburger dip
directions: Saute ground beef until browned; add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve with corn chips.
Yield: 1 quart.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until soft balls form in cold water.
Remove from heat. Add the peanuts or pecans.
Put back on heat and let form soft ball again.
Stir good.
Pour into buttered muffin pan or drop on wax paper.
Makes about 20 to 24.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Add soda, salt and baking powder. Sift again.
Cream shortening and add sugar gradually.
Beat again until light.
Add eggs and vanilla.

title: transparent pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and flour.
Add other ingredients. Bake in unbaked pie shell at 325°.

title: pink champagne dessert
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese well.
Add remaining ingredients. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill well.
Can also substitute 2 cups fresh or frozen strawberries for cherries.

title: no bake fudgies
directions: Combine in saucepan sugar, evaporated milk and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips.
Mix and stir until chocolate morsels are melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread in well greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
If desired, top pieces with walnut halves.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: any color slush
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water, lemonade and pineapple juice.
Freeze mixture until firm.
Remove from freezer and add lemon-lime soda.
Stir until slushy.

title: nell's turkey baste
directions: Mix all ingredients together and rub under skin of turkey, all over. Grease inside of brown bag. Place on a rack. Place turkey inside of bag. Close with paper clips. Put pan under rack and bake. After cooking appropriate time, remove bag and return to oven to brown.

title: favorite spaghetti sauce
directions: Boil noodles with salt and oil.
Layer with cream cheese. Layer noodles, sauce.
Repeat until out of stuff.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: coconut dessert
directions: Mix crackers with 1 stick of butter and 1 tablespoon of butter. Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix pudding with milk and coconut. Add ice cream. Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle coconut on top. Keep cool.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream
cheese
and
milk until fluffy.
Add peanut butter and blend.	Add
lemon juice and vanilla;
blend.
Fold in Cool Whip
and pour into prepared pie shell.
Top with more Cool Whip. Chill
until
set.	Will make 2 (8-inch) pies or 1 generous 10-inch pie.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Bring to a boil the oil, vinegar, celery seed, salt, dry mustard and 1 tablespoon of sugar.

title: judy's "apricot" jam
directions: Peel and grate the zucchini.
Add 1 cup water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 6 minutes.
Add the sugar, lemon juice and crushed pineapple.
Cook for 6 more minutes.
Add the Jell-O; mix well.
Pour into jars and seal, or cool and pour into plastic containers and freeze.
Makes about 4 plus pints.

title: pork sausage topping for baked potato
directions: Cook meat and onion until browned.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Place meat in dish, combine honey and next nine ingredients, stir well.
Pour over meat.
Cover and refrigerate over night, turning once or twice.
Grill or broil 25 - 35 minutes basting once or twice.

title: our famous pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Add syrups and chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Dip slices in milk, then in flour, then salt and pepper, then dip in 2 beaten eggs and then finally in bread crumbs.

title: aunt veronica's macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set 3 to 4 hours or overnight. Makes a large salad.

title: elote con crema(corn and cream)
directions: In a skillet, melt the butter and saute the onion and garlic until the onion is soft.
Add the chopped chiles, then the tomatoes.
Cook a minute to soften.
Add the corn, salt and pepper and saute briefly.
Reduce the heat to simmer and add the cream and cream cheese pieces.
Stir to melt the cheese and cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: grandmother's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar.
Add butter and eggs to other ingredients.
Add flour and stir.
Roll out like biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine shredded cabbage, shredded carrot and finely chopped, small onion in bowl.
Combine creamy Italian dressing and low-fat (1%) milk.
Mix with cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate.
Makes 4 servings.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across the grain into thin strips. Combine the soy sauce, garlic and ginger. Add the beef. Toss and set aside while chopping the vegetables.
Heat the oil in a frying pan or wok. Add the beef and toss over high heat until browned.
Taste the meat. If it is not tender, cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.
Turn the heat up and add the vegetables. Toss until crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix the cornstarch with the water.
Add to the pan.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add the tomatoes and heat through.
Preparation time:
20 minutes.
Cooking time:
30 to 40 minutes.

title: melon mousse
directions: In food processor, process melon until smooth.
In medium saucepan, combine gelatin, sugar and 1/3 cup of apple juice. Cook, stirring until mixture boils and gelatin and sugar are dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Stir in melon mixture.
Add yogurt and mint and mix well.
Pour into 4-cup mold or 4 ounce custard cups.
Refrigerate until set.

title: shrimp delight
directions: Saute onions, celery and green peppers in margarine until onions turn color.
Add mushrooms, soup and sour cream.
Mix well. Add shrimp and rice and pour into greased casserole.
Cover top with generous amount of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato cabbage soup
directions: In a large soup kettle, cook garlic, onion and cabbage in oil over low heat, stirring, until softened.
Add flour and stir and cook 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, water and seasonings.
Salt to taste.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer one hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix
together well.
Bake in 4 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 60 minutes or until brown and apart from sides of pan.
Drain and serve.
Will serve 6.

title: snow ball cake
directions: Bake cake as directed. Crumble up cake in little pieces into a bowl. Then add jello and crushed pineapple. Chill and then add cool whip on cake and then coconut.

title: chocolate icebox pie
directions: Mix flour, pecans and oleo together and spread on bottom of 9 x 13 baking pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Let cool.

title: sweet potatoes with apples
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender; drain and cool.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Alternate layers of potatoes and apples in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour orange juice over.
Mix sugar, ginger and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over potatoes and apples. Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until apples are done.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: granny's chocolate sauce
directions: In a small
saucepan,
combine
cocoa, flour, sugar and salt. Stir hot water
into mixture and cook over medium heat, stirring all the time,
until
thick,
clear
and smooth.
Add butter and vanilla.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 3/4 cups sauce.

title: mi sou
directions: Cut potatoes into French fry shapes.
Slice carrots.
Cook potatoes and carrots in skillet in small amount of oil.
Add Fry Chick, bamboo sprouts, sliced chestnuts and bean sprouts with liquid from cans.
Simmer on low.
Saute onion and celery; add to mixture.
Add cooked spaghetti and 1/4 to 1/2 cup of catsup.

title: low-fat spanish empanadas
directions: *I use Pillsbury All-Ready crusts.

title: cheesy peas
directions: Drain peas; save juice.
Heat soup, cheese with enough juice to keep from sticking.
Add peas and heat.

title: frosty strawberry dessert
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and spread in 9 x 13 pan evenly. Bake for 20 minutes. Stir occasionally while baking. Remove half for the top; leave the rest in the bottom of the pan.

title: turkey divan
directions: Combine hot water, butter and contents of vegetable seasoning packet in bowl; stir until butter is melted.
Add stuffing crumbs and stir until moistened.
Prepare broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Combine soup, milk and sherry in saucepan and bring just to a boil.
Place broccoli in shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Add a layer of turkey and top with the stuffing.
Pour soup mixture over stuffing.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade chili for hot dogs
directions: Brown ground beef; add other ingredients and mix well.

title: chicken and pastry
directions: Boil a whole chicken in 4 quarts of seasoned water (salt and pepper).
Remove fully cooked chicken; allow to cool, then debone. Remove approximately 2 to 3 cups of broth to make Pastry (Pastry recipe follows).
Reserve remaining broth to cook the Pastry.

title: cole slaw
directions: Place cabbage and pepper in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: pumpkin nut cookies
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add pumpkin, egg and extract; blend.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend with first mixture; stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Stir to dissolve.
Chill until partially set. Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: scalloped corn and green peppers
directions: Combine white sauce and egg; beat thoroughly. Add corn, sugar and green pepper. Pour into well oiled baking dish.
Cover with crumbs. Bake in hot oven (425°) until well browned. Makes 6 servings.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush wafers and pour milk over them.
Let stand while you cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time; then vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Fold in the wafer mix.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Melt butter in large frying pan.
Add 1 package seasoning mix from Stove Top dressing and cook a while on low.
Add dressing mix (minus the 1 package seasoning mix) and mix well.
Put half the mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with chicken chunks.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over chicken.
Top with rest of dressing.
Pour broth over top and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: bacon-wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Marinate water chestnuts in soy sauce at least 30 minutes. Drain and roll each in sugar.
Wrap each with bacon and secure with toothpick.
Bake on broiler pan at 400° for 30 minutes. Drain and serve warm.

title: booster club microwave caramel corn
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients for 3 minutes on High 9 or until margarine and marshmallows melt.
Add soda.
Stir.
Cook 30 seconds more.
Pour over popped corn.
Spread out to cool on cookie sheets.

title: marian's cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in boiling water.
Add flour and salt; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating vigorously after each egg is added.
Drop from 2 teaspoons, 2 inches apart, onto greased baking sheet.
Cook at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 25 minutes.
When cool, cut in half.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and saute onion.
Add chicken, tomato sauce, tomatoes, taco seasoning mix and garlic powder. Blend well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Place 4 tortillas in
9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour 1/3 of chicken mixture on tortillas, spreading evenly.
Layer 1/3 of the cheese and olives on top of chicken.
Repeat layers two times, ending with olives.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and casserole is heated through.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix well.
Add croutons to romaine lettuce or other salad greens and toss with dressing.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes 10 minutes.
Place in cold water.
Peel and slice crosswise into casserole.
Combine Dr. Pepper, sugar, butter and salt; bring to a boil.
Boil 10 minutes.
Pour over potatoes. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Baste potatoes several times with syrup as potatoes bake.

title: quick green bean casserole
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and garlic.
Add green beans; stir well.
Put in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine cracker crumbs, cheese and butter; sprinkle on casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with French fried onion rings or toasted sliced almonds.
Bake 10 additional minutes. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix 2 tablespoons of the thawed apple juice concentrate with the cornstarch. In a small saucepan, heat remaining concentrate. Blend in cornstarch mixture, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth. Stir in margarine and cinnamon. Pour thickened apple juice over apples; toss gently to coat. Sprinkle lightly with salt, if desired. Pour mixture into bottom of pie crust. Cover with top crust. Cut vents to allow steam to escape. Brush top with milk or margarine. Bake for 50 minutes or until done.

title: casa fiesta grand slam dip
directions: Note:
For added zest, garnish with picante salsa or taco sauce.

title: olive spread
directions: Mix together by hand in a mixing bowl the cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Combine with olives and onions.
Serve as a spread with assorted crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in casserole dish 30 minutes.

title: frozen passion
directions: Refrigerator-freezer method:
In large bowl combine ingredients.
Turn into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Freeze to a firm mush, about 1 hour.
Break into pieces and turn into large mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Return to pan.
Cover.
Freeze until firm.

title: cherry squares
directions: Crumble oats, flour and sugar together.
Cut in butter.
Pat half of the mixture into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover with pie filling.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: Place a layer of whole graham crackers on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Mix pudding and milk.
Put a layer over crackers. Top with a layer of crackers.
Cover crackers with commercial chocolate icing.

title: cinnamon coffee ring
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and 2 cups sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla; mix well. Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream. Spoon 1/3 of the batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Combine the cinnamon, nuts and remaining sugar. Sprinkle 1/3 over batter. Repeat layers twice. Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: cherry sundae
directions: Can use other fruits.

title: one pan magic cookie bars
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter.
Remove from heat. Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top with chocolate, coconut and nuts; press down gently. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool and cut into bars.

title: granny whatley's peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in baking dish.
Mix peaches with 1 cup sugar and pour into baking dish.
Mix 1 cup sugar, baking powder, flour and salt.
Add milk and stir for batter.
Pour batter over peaches.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Place in oblong Pyrex dish. Sprinkle with cilantro.
Pour over salsa; sprinkle cheese and olives.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with Spanish rice, refried beans and flour tortillas.

title: better-than-sex cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
When done, punch holes in cake with fork.
Cool.
Add sugar to pineapple.
(May add a little extra pineapple juice.)
Let simmer until hot, then pour over cake.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Pour over pineapple mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and refrigerate.
Serve with cherries on top.

title: fruited cheese salad
directions: In mixing bowl, blend together cottage cheese and thawed Cool Whip.
Beat until blended.
Stir in dry jello.
Fold in pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Press into 7 or 8 cup mold.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Makes 12 servings.

title: panas
directions: Scald and scrape hair from pig's head.
Skinned head is not as good.
Put head in large kettle and boil until meat falls off the bone.
Remove meat and grind together with onions.
Cool broth and skim off lard.
Put ground meat and onions back into broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Boil this and stir in flour until the meat leaves the sides of the kettle.
Then put meat mixture in bread loaf pans until thoroughly cooled.
Take out of pans, wrap and freeze.

title: shrimp orleans
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Add onion and garlic salt.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Blend soup, sour cream and catsup.
Stir into onion mixture.
Add mushrooms and shrimp.
Cover.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, until mixture is heated through, approximately 10 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Stir in paste, mushrooms, oregano, salt and pepper with browned meat and onion.
Let all ingredients simmer.
Press 1 can of biscuits into a greased pie pan to form crust.
Spoon in meat mixture.
Sprinkle top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: polly's okie cornbread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; blend until smooth.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Smooth sour cream over top carefully (add 1 tablespoon milk to spread easier).
Sprinkle on onions, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes or more.
Freeze if desired.
Serves 8.

title: good punch
directions: Add the spice bag to cider, cover and heat very slowly to the boiling point.
Remove from heat and serve steaming hot.

title: spicy apple syrup(serve this warm over ice cream, pancakes or crepes.)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in 1 1/2-quart saucepan and stir over medium heat until mixture simmers and clears, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve warm.
Refrigerate any remaining syrup in jar. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: basic brownies
directions: In medium bowl, beat together eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla until light.
Add melted butter.
Beat until blended.
Mix in flour and cocoa at low speed.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in greased 8-inch microwave dish.
Microwave 6 to 7 minutes.
Rotate 1/4 turn after 3 minutes.

title: ginger carrots
directions: Scrub carrots and slice into coins.
Cook until tender.
Melt butter in saucepan; add orange juice and other ingredients.
Bring just to a boil (it thickens); mix into drained, cooked carrots.

title: red bean salad
directions: Drain the beans. Slice the onion thinly. Slice the eggs. Combine all ingredients and refrigerate 4 hours.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix soups (don't dilute),
onion soup mix and red wine. Stir in beef cubes.
Place in an ovenproof casserole, covered, or a covered roaster.
Bake
for about 2 to 3 hours. Stir and serve with noodles or rice.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Put buttermilk, white sugar
and
soda
in
large
pot. Stir mixture until sugar
is
completely dissolved.
Place pot on a low to medium burner and
let
candy
boil to a soft ball stage.
Stir constantly.
The
mixture
will
turn
a brownish color, but don't worry, it's supposed
to.
Once the soft ball stage is reached (by testing in
cold
water),
remove the pot from the
heat.
Add
2 cups pecan halves, vanilla and butter. Beat mixture briskly until it becomes glossy and starts to get very
thick.
Quickly
spoon onto greased waxed paper, making little
patties.
Let
candy completely
cool before removing from the
paper.
Should
the mixture harden before you've had time to get it onto paper, return to heat for a few seconds.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Clean and devein shrimp.
Set aside.
In frypan, cook onion and green pepper in butter until limp.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer over low heat 12 to 15 minutes or until shrimp are firm and pink, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix
together.	Pour
into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: onion ritzy casserole
directions: Boil onions in saucepan for a few minutes until transparent; drain well.
Put in glass casserole dish; dot with butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Crush crackers over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fudgy zucchini brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat an 8-inch pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Melt chocolate and butter in the top of a double boiler.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add egg, salt, baking powder and vanilla; mix until well combined.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken. Debone and cut into bite size pieces. In large baking dish place layer of dressing mix.
Melt butter and drizzle on dressing mix.
Add layer of chicken, 1 can mushroom soup, 1 can (10-oz.) chicken broth from boiled chicken. Add another layer of dressing mix, then add can of cream of chicken soup and 1 can (10-oz.) chicken broth.
Sprinkle remaining dressing mix on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 12-14.

title: sausage snacks
directions: The best way to mix them and form balls is with your hands. Bake in broiler pan with rack in it so the balls can drain as they bake.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: erin's chicken chili
