directions: Chop peppers and onion and mash garlic.
In 6-quart Dutch oven over medium heat in hot oil, cook peppers, onion and garlic until tender.
Add chicken, chili powder, sugar and ground red pepper. Cook until chicken is no longer pink.
Add stewed tomatoes with their liquid, beans with their liquid and green chilies with their liquid.
Over high heat, bring to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-low, add can of beer (chef may drink some first); simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: curried summer squash soup
directions: In large casserole or soup pot, cook onions in butter until light golden.
Stir in curry powder.
Add squash and stir to coat with butter.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: bean salsa
directions: Mix together and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Put all ingredients together, except graham cracker crusts. Put 1/2 mix in 1 crust and half in the other. Will set up 1 hour or less.

title: batter-fried mushrooms
directions: Add mushrooms and small amount of water.
Keep adding small amounts of water until you have a good batter.
Drop by spoonfuls into a frying pan (do not deep fry).
Fry until a golden brown on each side.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Have water boiling in bottom of double boiler.
Place all ingredients in top pan.
Place in bottom pan; reduce heat.
Beat over heat 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat 5 more minutes.

title: four layer dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, chopped nuts and butter for crust. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: 11-minute fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, stirring constantly. Cook 11 minutes after boiling begins.
Remove from heat. Add balance of ingredients and beat well. Pour into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2 pan or baking dish. Let set overnight in cool place. Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: hasty hash
directions: In a microwavable skillet, saute bacon; drain and crumble. Pour off drippings.
Add onion to skillet; brown in skillet.
Add potatoes, bacon and meat.
Microwave on High until warmed through. Add seasonings; stir and let stand.
Invert onto serving platter. Top with prepared eggs.
Serve with chili sauce and toasted muffins.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until foamy.
Add sugar gradually.
Continue beating until very stiff.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Turn into a greased pie plate, making a nest like shell building up sides above pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Cool completely.

title: strawberry delight
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan mix crushed pretzels, sugar and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Mix frozen strawberries, strawberry jello and boiling water.
Stir until jello is dissolved. Pour over pretzels and chill.
Mix cream cheese and sugar and beat well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put on top of strawberry mixture. Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours before serving.

title: sauerbraten meatballs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Brown in margarine in a large skillet over medium heat. Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Mix well.
Pour over meat balls.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Remove meatballs to a service plate and keep warm. Strain sauce; stir in soup.
Pour over meatballs.
Serves 4.

title: roberts corn dip
directions: Mix together; refrigerate 3 hours or overnight. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: country breakfast
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook potatoes in margarine until partially thawed.
Add green pepper and onion and continue cooking until lightly browned.
Season to taste.
Break eggs over potato mixture. Cover; cook until eggs are done.
Top with cheese.
Cover; continue cooking until cheese is melted.
Mushrooms or green chiles may be added.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cheesy broccoli-n-mushroom bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange broccoli in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Whisk together soup, salad dressing and milk.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese and croutons.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: low-fat cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until creamy.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
4 grams fat per serving.

title: chocolate-coconut dessert
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate in milk.
Bring to boiling.
Boil gently, uncovered, 4 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add marshmallows; heat and stir until melted.
Chill.

title: pecan nut cake
directions: Note:
Reserve 1 cup flour for nuts and raisins.

title: double treat cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and peanut butter until creamy. Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Add vanilla and chocolate chips. Stir until well mixed.

title: gourmet mustard
directions: Whisk eggs in, one at a time; whisk thoroughly. Then add sugar, butter and salt. Keep stirring, about 5 minutes. Do not overcook or eggs will curdle.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients; put in hand-cranked or electric ice cream maker and process.

title: salmon puffs
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Slowly add buttermilk and beaten eggs.
Crumble salmon and add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoons into deep fat.
They will begin to puff as soon as they are in the hot fat.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain by placing on paper towel.
Makes about 15 puffs.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and shortening together. Add sugar, a little at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture alternately with milk.
Start with flour and end with flour.
Add vanilla. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: low-fat strawberry vanilla pudding
directions: Place cubed cake in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Combine pudding, milk and frozen yogurt.
Pour over cake.
Dissolve Jell-O in water; add frozen strawberries.
Pour over yogurt mixture. Chill until set; top with Cool Whip.

title: crispy oven fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, egg white and milk to make batter.
Dip chicken into batter; then coat with corn flake crumbs (seasoned to taste). Bake for 1 hour at 350° in uncovered baking dish, coated with vegetable oil spray.
Makes 4 servings.
Low in fat!

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine and cook over low heat to 240°.
Remove and cool to 110°.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat.
Spread on buttered dish or pan.

title: cool whip delight
directions: In a large bowl, mix Cool Whip and dry jello. Mix thoroughly. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute the vegetables in the oil.
Mix in the tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer 15 to 30 minutes.
Add the shrimp and heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot rice.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix potatoes with flour, onion, eggs, salt and pepper. Mixture will resemble bread dough. Add about 1/4-inch oil in skillet. Drop potato mixture from tablespoon. Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides. Drain on paper towel. Goes good with green vegetables.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and zucchini.
Beat; add flour, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda that has been sifted together.
Mix in with mixture well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: shrimp salad dip
directions: Heat tomato soup, gelatine and salt.
Beat cream cheese and add to mixture.
Then add mayonnaise, celery, onion and shrimp. Chill.

title: blueberry pizza dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine cake mix, 1 cup oats and 6 tablespoons margarine until crumbly. (A pastry blender mixes this well.) Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping. Blend egg into remaining crumbs. Press into a "Pampered Chef" deep-dish baker or a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, forming a short rim. Bake for 12 minutes.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Heat milk until lukewarm.
Add sugar, salt and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add to yeast.
Add flour.
Stir well, but dough will be sticky.
Let rise in a warm place for 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Mix first 6
ingredients
and
mix with last 5 ingredients. Mix well.
Grease
and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.	Freezes well.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.

Cover with water. Cook on high for 5 to 6 hours or until meat is done. Pour water off roast. Tear meat into pieces and return to crock-pot. Add rest of ingredients and let simmer until the flavor is absorbed by the meat.

title: vanilla peach cream
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions, using only 1 1/2 cups milk.
Lightly
cover surface with plastic wrap, cool. Beat in
sour cream until smooth, stir in peaches and vanilla. Chill until ready to serve.
This dessert will keep in the refrigerator a few days.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole with a tight lid.
Cook in a 250° oven for 5 hours.
Do not stir.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, then add mashed, hard-cooked eggs.
Heat milk and cornstarch.
Add to crab mixture and form into balls.
Roll in cracker crumbs; dip into egg-milk mixture, then into cracker crumbs again.
Fry in deep fat.

title: grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large shallow container; stir well.
Add tenderloin, turning to coat.
Cover and marinate (in refrigerator) 8 hours.
Remove tenderloin from marinade.
Grill 6 inches from hot coals for 20 to 35 minutes or until done, turning often.

title: quickbread holiday fruit cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom and sides of 12 cup fluted tube pan or 10-inch angel food pan in large bowl. Combine eggs and water.
Add remaining ingredients by hand.
Stir until combined.
Pour in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 to 85 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool for 30 minutes.
Loosen edges and remove from pan.
Cool completely.
To store, wrap lightly in foil or plastic wrap.
If desired, glaze with corn syrup.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Crush noodles (with rolling pin).
Brown sesame seeds, almonds and noodles in 350° oven.
Stir often with wooden spoon; cool. Mix onions with cabbage.
Add noodle mixture to salad just before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into large casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly and potatoes are tender.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add flour mixed with carbonated ammonia.
Mix in coconut; roll into balls about walnut-size.
Bake in 300° oven for about 4 or 5 minutes.

title: nina's speedy rolls
directions: Combine water, sugar and yeast. Add salt and 2 C flour. Beat 2 minutes with mixer.

title: ho ho bars(makes 35 bars)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put in greased 11 x 15-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: aunt willie's pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix.
Pour into pie shells; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked green bean bundles
directions: Cut bacon strips in half.
Wrap bacon around about 8 or 9 whole beans and secure with toothpick.
Place bundles in a casserole dish.
Drizzle 1 tablespoon of barbecue sauce on each bundle.
Cover with foil. Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: basic pasta dough
directions: Sift together flour and salt into a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of the flour, one at a time.
Add 1 egg, mixing slightly after each additional egg.
Gradually add water a tablespoon at a time.
Mix well to make a stiff dough.
Turn dough onto a well-floured clean surface.
Knead well.
Proceed and roll out or cut for pasta recipe.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cook for 40 minutes and pour in hot jars.

title: cheesy ham sandwich
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the ham, cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Place 1/3 cup mixture on bottom of each bun.
Wrap individually in foil.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and cheese spread begins to melt.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: red grape salad
directions: Drain the pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Set pineapple aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat juice, cream cheese, and mayonnaise until fluffy.
Stir in pineapple, marshmallows, and grapes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Serve or refrigerate.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in separate bowls using 2 cups boiling water each for lime and strawberry and 1 cup for lemon. Stir marshmallows into lemon Jell-O and set aside.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one.
Sift flour and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and mix.
Place in a 13-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix peas and soup;
add eggs and chopped pimento.
Pour into a
casserole
dish.
Garnish
with	cheese.
Bake
until cheese is lightly brown at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: golden pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients. Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed, 2 to 3 minutes. Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or 3 greased 5 1/2 x 3-inch mini-loaf pans. Bake for 45 to 55 minutes for 9 x 5-inch loaf or 30 to 35 minutes for mini loaves or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan. Cool completely. Store refrigerated.

title: cheese 'n beef pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In frying pan, brown meat and pepper; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato paste and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Separate crescent dough and place in ungreased 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Press over bottom and sides to form crust. Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese over crust.
Spoon half of hot meat mixture into crust.
Top with some Mozzarella cheese.
Spoon remaining meat mixture over cheese and top with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Place remaining Mozzarella cheese on top and melt.

title: unstuffed green pepper soup
directions: Simmer for 1 hour, before adding the cooked rice. Heat through again.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, margarine and sugar well.
Pat into a 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat together cream cheese and 10x sugar.
Put on top of cooled crust.
Prepare two boxes of lemon pudding.
Spread on top of cheese mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with Cool Whip.
Cut and serve.

title: mexicali dinner salad
directions: Chop tomatoes, onion and head of lettuce.
Add cheese and browned, drained beef.
Add seasonings, can of drained kidney beans and crushed tortilla chips.
Toss with French dressing. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Looks terrible.
Tastes great!

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes.
Drain and mash with butter.
Add all other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes or until knife when inserted comes out clean. Let cool and serve.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add chicken and soups.
Mix well.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: shrimp in beer
directions: Wash and dry shrimp.
Saute shrimp and onion in butter 1 minute on each side.
Add salt to taste, Tabasco and flour.
Mix well.
Remove from heat and add beer and lemon juice, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil; add bay leaf and thyme.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: "tasty taco salad"
directions: Drain kidney beans and rinse well with cold water; then drain on paper towel.
Brown beef in skillet; drain grease from pan. Then add salt, beans and taco seasoning mix.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Toss lettuce, onion, cheese, tortilla chips, avocado and tomatoes.
Then toss both mixtures together.
Garnish with additional tortilla chips.
Pour in Thousand Island dressing, toss lightly again and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 can of French fried onions. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions and bake uncovered 5 minutes or until golden.

title: stuffed mirlitons
directions: Cut mirlitons in
half lengthwise.
Place in large pot; cover with water.
Cover and
bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook slowly 20 to
minutes or until tender.	Remove halves and cool slightly.
Scoop
out pulp with a spoon, leaving firm shell about 1/4-inch thick.
Mash pulp and set aside.

title: microwave chile
directions: Combine meat, onion and celery in 3-quart casserole dish. Microwave on High 6 to 9 minutes or until meat is cooked and vegetables are tender.
Drain fat and break up meat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Microwave on High 5 minutes. Stir.
Reduce power to 50%.
Microwave, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes, stirring twice.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly. Stir in shredded zucchini and salad oil.
Stir egg mixture; add at once into flour mixture until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Spoon into cupcake pan lined with cupcake holders and bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in bottom of 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix remaining ingredients together and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.

title: charlie's barbecue eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Take muffin pan and line each cup with 1 slice of bacon.
Place pan and bacon in oven and cook until bacon is about 1/2 done (10 to 15 minutes).
Remove from oven and break 1 egg into each section.
Add all of the following seasonings and sauce on top of each egg:
salt and pepper, A.1. sauce, picante sauce, Lea & Perrins, dash of onion flakes, catsup, barbecue sauce, soy sauce and dash of Season-All.
Return to oven and cook until eggs are firm.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Chop pepper, onion and celery, then saute with meat until meat is white.
Add all other ingredients, including liquids.
Simmer 45 minutes with lid on or until it is the consistency you like. Delicious with corn bread.

title: shirley's devil's food cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch layer cake pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine dry ingredients
in
a
large
mixing bowl. Add milk, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Blend ingredients
at low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour
into
pans.
Bake
at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers and
35 to 40 minutes for the
larger
cake pan
or use cake
tester
method.
Cool
10 minutes.
Then remove from pans
and
cool
completely.
Frost with Mocha Cream Frosting or
chocolate frosting.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: authentic new orleans pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to soft ball stage (238° to 240°).
Remove from heat; stir until cooled and thickened.
Spoon out on buttered wax paper or foil.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on the box and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together rhubarb, margarine, Jell-O and sugar.
Sprinkle over cake and bake at 350° until cake tests done.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Cut meat in bite size pieces.
Coat meat in flour mixture.
Brown meat in butter.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add water to mushroom liquid to make 1 cup.
Heat to boiling.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot mixture.
Pour over meat.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Combine tomato sauce, green pepper and mushrooms.
Pour over meat.
Continue to bake for 15 minutes.

title: spicy baked shrimp
directions: Combine garlic, butter, salt, tarragon, marjoram and Tabasco. Cream together.
Add bread crumbs and toss until shrimp are well coated.
Bake in single layer at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley if desired before baking.
After baked, lightly squeeze lemon wedges over shrimp.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add the 1 cup boiling water.
Boil 2 minutes.
Cool.
Pour 1-quart unsweetened whole strawberries in mixture.
Pour int bake pie shell.
Add whipped topping.

title: lemon chewies
directions: Mix cake mix and 1 egg in a large bowl.
After mixing well with a spoon, add 2 cups Cool Whip.
Mix this until well blended. It will be very hard to stir.
Drop teaspoon of dough at a time into confectioners sugar and make into a ball.
Put on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° until lightly brown on bottom, about 8 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all
ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls in a deep fryer.
Let brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cracker crumbs.
Pour in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese with fork.
Chop green onions and ham. Mix onions and ham with cream cheese.
Serve with snack crackers or on celery sticks.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cut baked potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Place half in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. sprinkle with half of the salt, pepper and crumbled bacon.
Top with half of sour cream and cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 20 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Top with chopped green onions.

title: peppered beef brisket
directions: Trim all fat from beef. Spread pepper on wax paper and place brisket on pepper. Turn to coat all sides with the pepper. Combine remaining ingredients. Place brisket in a shallow dish and pour marinade over it. Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning meat occasionally. When ready to cook, line a large pan with foil. Place the brisket in the pan and pour marinade over meat. Cover with another large piece of foil and securely fold it into the bottom foil to seal. Bake at 300 degrees for 3 hours, or until tender.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Cook tomatoes, onions and peppers until soft.
Press through food mill.
Cook rapidly until thick, about 1 hour.
Tie whole spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Add sugar and salt to tomato mixture. Cook gently about 25 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add vinegar and paprika and cook until thick.
As mixture thickens, stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Pour boiling hot into sterilized jars leaving 1/8-inch headspace.
Yields 3 pints.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Layer in order and heat in 350° oven.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Brown chicken in butter and lemon juice.
Take up chicken. Add broth, flour, sherry and Worcestershire sauce to the butter and lemon juice mixture.
Slow cook until it begins to thicken. Put chicken, skin side down, in a baking dish.
Pour liquid mixture on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in buttered baking dish.
Add soup and water.
Stir.
Add precooked wild rice.
Bake covered at 350° until liquid is absorbed, about 1 hour.
Use a 2 to 3 quart baking dish.

title: honey zucchini bread
directions: Beat together first 6 ingredients, then add the rest.
Grease and flour 3 bread pans.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 300°. Remove from oven and brush with butter.

title: kesling korn
directions: Immerse corn (in shuck with silks) in water for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from water and place on preheated medium-high grill.
Turn 1/4 turn when shuck turns light brown (approximately 5 minutes, depending on grill).
Remove from grill and shuck corn (silks will just fall off with shucks).
Season to taste.
Enjoy!

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: In buttered 9 x 13-inch pan, put broccoli and chicken pieces. Blend the rest of the ingredients and spread over chicken mixture. Sprinkle on 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese. Spread the bread crumbs over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: french pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk.
Stir until smooth.
Add eggs. On hot griddle, pour 1/4 cup mixture (will be thin).
Turn once. Remove; spread with butter.
Sprinkle powdered sugar, then roll up.
You can also use jams or syrup.

title: beef rice casserole
directions: Combine onion soup, consomme and rice; sprinkle with garlic powder.
Add mushrooms.
Melt butter and pour over casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: turtle cheesecake
directions: In small bowl combine caramel topping, chocolate chips and pecans.
Spread in bottom of pie crust.
In small bowl beat together cream cheese, egg and sugar until smooth.
Gently spread over caramel mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Leftovers will need to be refrigerated.

title: breakfast fruit 'n biscuits
directions: Combine all fruit in large bowl.
Cover and chill thoroughly. Serve over hot biscuits or in a sherbet glass.
Make sure strawberries have thawed before serving.
Can be made the night before, but do not add the bananas until morning.
Serve with "HOT" biscuits.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Pour hominy into lightly greased baking dish.
Make a layer of Fritos, followed by a layer of 3/4 cup cheese.
Pour chili over cheese; top with remaining 3/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sharon polliard's salsa
directions: Combine ingredients in food processor until salsa is coarsely blended.
All ingredients can be adjusted to suit individual preferences.
Oh-Lay!

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Grind package of cranberries fine.
Grind 1 orange, peeling and all.
Prepare raspberry jello as directed.
Add sugar, a little less water on jello directions.
Add cold jello to mixture.
Mix all together.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Bring soda to a boil in a saucepan, preferably heatproof glass or stainless steel.
Remove from heat.
Add tea bags.
Cover and let steep 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags and add lemon juice, sweetener, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Return pan to low heat. Keep just below simmer for at least 30 minutes.
This allows the flavors to blend.
Hold longer if desired.
Serve hot with a lemon slice in each cup or glass.
Makes 5 servings.

title: tuna stuffed mushroom  caps
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Carefully remove stems from caps.
Chop stems. Melt 1 tablespoon butter in frying pan.
Saute chopped stems. Cool.
Drain tuna.
Separate into small pieces in bowl with fork. Mix in onion, celery and cooked stems.
Add mayonnaise or salad dressing until mixture holds together, but is not loose.
Chill.

title: pasta and sausage
directions: Saute sausage in oil for 5 minutes.
Add onion and cook until golden.
Add wine and cook until evaporated.
Add broth and peas; cook for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and a dash or two of basil. Remove from heat.
Stir in pasta and sprinkle with cheese to serve.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in milk; set aside.
In large bowl, stir all other ingredients, except melted butter or margarine.
Stir in liquid mixture.

title: pea salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Layer celery, onions and peas over lettuce. Mix sugar and mayonnaise.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: yum yum fudge
directions: Prepare the first 6 ingredients beforehand.
Cook sugar and milk.
Boil hard 5 minutes.
When done, stir in prepared ingredients until smooth.

title: banana nuggets
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit punch slush
directions: Puree the bananas in a food processor, along with the thawed lemonade.
Then add the orange juice, pineapple juice, sugar and water; mix well.
This mixture is frozen and will fit in a gallon plastic milk jug.
Before serving, partially thaw and add the ginger ale and lemon-lime soft drink.
Yields 50 (1/2 cup) servings.
You can reduce amount of sugar.

title: boiled cauliflower(kokt blomkaal)
directions: Remove cauliflower's large outer leaves.
Cut the stalk off to about 1-inch and cut a deep cross on the end to make it cook quicker.
Bring water and salt to boil.
Put cauliflower in, head up, and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove cauliflower from boiling water and pour cold water over it to cool it.
(This keeps the cauliflower white.)
Place cauliflower back into the boiling water, head down this time, and boil for about 20 minutes, being careful not to overcook.
Serve cauliflower on a platter with melted butter poured over it and sprinkled with parsley.
Save water and any leftovers for cauliflower soup.

title: beefy mexican soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and green pepper until beef is done.
Drain.
Stir in sauce mix, water, chili powder, garlic salt, salt and tomatoes (with liquid). Break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and corn (with liquid). Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Garnish with corn chips, if desired.

title: party brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in the eggs.
Blend in cocoa.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; cut into 16 squares.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Precook vermicelli for	5
minutes;
cool.
Beat
eggs, canned milk, milk, sugar and
extract.
Butter
and flour 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan.	Put
vermicelli
in
Pyrex and add liquids. Bake at 425° for 1 hour or until done.
Delicious as side dish or just dessert.

title: fruit 'n pudding salad
directions: Use liquid from oranges and pineapple.
Then add enough water to make 3 cups.
Cook both boxes of pudding, using the 3 cups of liquid.
Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add oranges, pineapple and bananas.
Stir.
Top with cherries.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: jiffy hamburger soup
directions: Simmer all for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil, pineapple and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in sweet potatoes and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lickety-split vegetable dip
directions: In blender, process yogurt, cottage cheese, onion flakes, garlic powder, dill weed, sugar and salt until creamy.
Pour into containers; cover and chill overnight to blend flavors.
Will keep in the refrigerator for several days.
tags: assortment of carrot and celery sticks

title: szechwan green beans
directions: Spray a wok or skillet with nonstick spray.
Pour a tablespoon cooking oil into the wok, under a low flame or heat.
When oil becomes hot, add the green beans and some onions.
Stir.
After about 3 minutes, add the rest of the green beans and onions. Continue to stir.
After about 2 minutes, add all the mushrooms (if you want broccoli florets, add them now).
Continue to periodically stir until the rawness has left the vegetables.
Chop up the chilli peppers into very small sections and add them to the wok.
Stir. Add the remaining ingredients except for the cornstarch.
Stir for 30 seconds and cover for 3 minutes.
Lift cover and gradually add the cornstarch and stir (this will produce a gravy).
When the gravy is at the consistency you like, serve and enjoy.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Mix softened margarine and sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs and beat in flour, pineapple, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Cook at 325° until golden brown.

title: ginger soy dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered container.
Great on spinach salad.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together, put in 11 x 7 inch dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, 1/2 envelope taco seasoning and medium taco sauce.
Layer in pan the cream cheese mixture with the mild taco sauce, Mozzarella cheese, lettuce and tomato.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: salmon spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, with other ingredients except the salmon.
Drain and flake salmon and gently fold into cream cheese mixture.
Chill overnight or at least 4 hours.
Serve with crackers and vegetable sticks.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar, butter and marshmallows; microwave for 4 minutes.
Stir and microwave for 1 1/2 minutes more.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla; stir until blended.
Pour into pie plate; cool and cut.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Prepare vegetables and salt (first 5 ingredients); mix well and let stand overnight.
In A.M. drain and rinse in cold water. Drain well.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add flavoring and milk. Alternate between flour and eggs until all used (flour should be used last).
Spray tube pan with Pam.
Bake in 300° oven for 2 hours or until toothpick clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Put on cake rack to finish cooling.

title: coffee punch
directions: Add sugar to hot coffee.
Cool.
Add ice cream and whipped cream.
Serve.

title: cajun shrimp creole
directions: In large, deep	fry
pan
over medium heat, melt butter and oil.
Add
celery, garlic, onion and bell pepper.
Saute 4 minutes, until
vegetables	begin to soften.
Add stewed tomatoes and tomato	sauce.	Mix well.
Add basil, pepper, cayenne pepper and salt.
Mix
well.
Over medium-high heat, simmer 10 minutes. Add shrimp.
Simmer
to	8 minutes, stirring frequently, until shrimp
are pink and cooked thoroughly.
Serve over white or brown rice.

title: etouffee
directions: Cook celery, onion, pepper, butter until very soft, add garlic; continue cooking for 10 minutes.
Add flour and cook 3 more minutes, stirring to keep form sticking.
Add Rotel tomatoes, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add meat and cook 20 to 30 more minutes. Serve with rice and crusty French bread.

title: chili-oodles
directions: In large saucepan, cook meat and onion until meat is almost done; drain.
Add green pepper and garlic; cook until green pepper is just tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except pasta. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Serve chili over hot pasta.
Makes 6 servings (1 3/4 cups each).

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Thoroughly mix ground beef, onion, garlic, corn flakes and eggs; season to taste.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Combine remaining ingredients into crock-pot.
Brown meat balls in broiler on both sides.
Place meat balls into crock-pot and mix with sauce.
Cook in crock-pot until meat balls are done.
Yields 65.

title: taco corn chip dip
directions: Layer refried beans on bottom.
Fry ground chuck, drain and add taco seasoning.
Then layer, salsa, Velveeta and sour cream. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can add peppers.
Serve warm; eat with corn chips.

title: sour cream and chives dip
directions: Saute onions in butter. Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Roll into 1-inch balls. Freeze 1 hour before cooking. Place frozen balls on baking sheet. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and garlic in big pan with oil.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce with seasonings, then simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
When almost done, boil water and cook noodles.
Pour meat mixture in bottom of big flat pan to cover bottom.
Cover with noodles and cottage cheese, Swiss cheese and Parmesan.
Cover then with noodles and rest of cottage cheese and Parmesan, then rest of sauce.
Top with Swiss cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: snow drift mardi gras
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add sugar, eggs and flour; blend well.
Stir cake mix and nuts in 1/4 cup flour.
Add to batter. Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 70 to 80 minutes in a Bundt pan.

title: cottage cheese dressing
directions: Combine cottage cheese, sweetener and lemon juice in blender container.
Blend until creamy.
Add milk a tablespoon at a time until of desired consistency.
Makes 1 cup.

title: baked hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until blended.
Place one tablespoon of batter into well-greased muffin tins.
Place tins on sheet of aluminum foil the size of the pan to prevent overbrowning.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 44 hush puppies.

title: caesar salad with homemade croutons
directions: *Homemade Croutons:
Heat olive oil in heavy skillet. Cut Italian or French bread into 3/4-inch squares.
Place into hot oil.
Add minced clove of fresh garlic. Stir until browned evenly. Remove from heat and let cool in a cloth napkin or light towel.

title: party punch
directions: Freeze juice.
Juice and strain lemons.
Put in jar with 2 cups sugar and stir occasionally.
Put in refrigerator.
Combine frozen juice, lemon mixture and water.
Mix well.
Add ice cream and more sugar if needed.

title: gran's marble cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except syrup and chips.
Divide batter into thirds.
Put one third in well greased stem pan.
Mix syrup and chips with one third batter and spoon on layer in pan.
Top with remaining third batter.
Pull a knife through to marbleize. Bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Dribble with glaze of chocolate chips, margarine, confectioners sugar and milk.

title: orange glazed chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side up, in a foil-lined baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients and brush on chicken.
Continue baking and basting for another 30 to 40 minutes.
Ten minutes before chicken is done, pour on more honey to taste.
Serve with honey.

title: sweet fruit slaw
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Thin mayonnaise with reserved juice.
Mix well into slaw mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: peach tea
directions: Boil 2 cups water.
Place tea bags in gallon pitcher.
Pour boiling water over tea. Steep for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags and fill pitcher with water. Sweeten to taste.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Combine wine, soy sauce, honey and chicken parts in a plastic bag.
Marinate 1 hour, turning bag to mix contents.
Place chicken parts, marinade and water chestnuts in a micro-safe casserole and micro-cook on High power 9 to 12 minutes.
Rearrange chicken parts and micro-cook on High power for another 9 to 12 minutes or until done.
Test for doneness by piercing with a fork. Juices should run clear, not pink.
Place chicken on a serving platter.
Cover with foil to keep warm.
Combine water and cornstarch; stir into pan juices and micro-cook on High power 2 to 3 minutes or until thickened.
Stir occasionally during cooking. Pour over chicken and serve.

title: cayenne cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll in nuts and refrigerate.
Great with Club crackers.

title: crab souffle
directions: Trim crusts from Pepperidge Farm type bread and cut into cubes.
Place 1/2 of bread in a greased 3-quart casserole.
Mix other ingredients, except for milk and eggs and spread on top of bread cubes.
Add remaining cubes and the rest of the mix.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over casserole and place in refrigerator, at least overnight (12 hours).
Just before baking top with cheese and paprika.
Have casserole at room temperature and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cheese custard pie
directions: Blend cheese, sugar and eggs.
Add salt and lemon rind.
Add milk and cream.
Pour into pastry lined pan and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil. Cook until browned.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together and store in an airtight container.
Add 2 rounded teaspoons in 1 cup of hot water.
Serve and enjoy.

title: corn custard
directions: Mix ingredients as given.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° until firm and lightly browned.

title: crab casserole dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk; blend in crabmeat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm over crackers.

title: pop's gourmet rice pudding
directions: In top of double boiler, combine rice, water and salt.
Cook over medium heat about 40 minutes or until rice is tender.
Do not drain.
Stir in condensed milk, raisins and butter.
Cook, stirring frequently, until slightly thickened, about 20 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add raisins and vanilla.
Serve warm or cold. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Stir all together and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Place 1/2 cup cheese over the top to melt as it cooks.

title: zucchini raisin spice cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat together the eggs, brown sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat in the dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in the zucchini and raisins.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar.
Serves 8.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind the first 3 ingredients and cover with salt and boiling water for 10 minutes.
Squeeze all the water out and add remaining ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes; stir to keep from burning and seal in pint jars.

title: mexican dish
directions: Cook ground beef with onion.
Heat pintos and corn in saucepan.
Heat enchilada sauce and tomato sauce in saucepan.

title: excellent pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out on floured board.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook beef until brown.
Add garlic salt, chili mix and tomatoes.
Simmer until almost dry.
Dip meat mixture into large serving dish.
Heat soup and milk or Velveeta and spread over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with olives, onions, cheese and Fritos. Garnish with lettuce and tomato wedges.
Serves 10 people.
Can be prepared in 30 minutes.
Serve with favorite rice.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and water.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in peanuts gradually so as not to lose the boil.
Keep a rolling boil until peanuts pop and turn brown.
Remove from heat.
Add soda, stirring well.
Add salt.
Pour on a well-greased platter.
Allow room for candy to spread.
When cold, break into clumps.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheeses; mix in chili.
Stays hot in a crock-pot.

title: johnna's cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrot.
Mix well remaining ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cabbage and carrot.

title: green beans with sesame seed and mushrooms
directions: Cook green beans until half done; add mushrooms.
Continue cooking until both are tender and done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Boil for 5 more minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute
meat
in butter for about 1 minute on each side; set aside.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter until golden brown, then
return meat to pan.
Add sour cream and a couple dashes of Worcestershire sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Warm thoroughly;
do
not
boil.
Serve over noodles or thick fried potatoes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Prebake pie shell on preheated cookie sheet in a 450° oven for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 375°.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or processor; beat until smooth.
Heat 1 to 2 inches of oil in small skillet.
Pour 1/2 cup batter into funnel.
Hold funnel over skillet and start in the middle.
Release batter in slow circular motion toward outside of skillet.
Fry until golden on bottom; flip over and fry until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat the ingredients; pour into a greased pie plate.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 20 minutes.

title: hash and cheese pizzas
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; spread on muffin halves.
Broil 8 to 10 inches from heat until lightly browned.
Crisscross cheese strips on top.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: mom's nut bread
directions: Cream eggs, oleo and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add salt and baking soda to the flour.
Alternately add flour and sour milk to creamed mixture.
Batter will have a cake batter like consistency.
Add your ground walnuts.
Pour batter into three greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Doneness: Check as you would a cake.
Will make three loaves if baked in 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pans.

title: dumplings
directions: Drop spoonfuls into salted boiling water.
When they float to the top, they are done.

title: mt. sterling frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend all ingredients.	Pour in cupcake papers inserted in cupcake
pan.
Freeze.
(Place
in freezer bag for storage and
to be used later.) Remove individual salads as needed and serve
on bed
of
lettuce.
Top with sour cream or any other desired topping.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all together by hand in bowl.
Put into a greased 8 x 10-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350°.
Watch very closely, for it will burn easily.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pudding and pineapple.
Fold in marshmallows, chopped nuts and Cool Whip.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: eggplant patrice
directions: Slice
unpeeled eggplant about 1/4 inch thick.
Parboil until partially tender.
Place a layer of eggplant slices in a 13 x
9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add a layer of tomatoes.
Fill spaces with a
mixture
of chopped pepper and chopped onions. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add a layer of cheese.
Repeat layers until casserole is filled.
End with cheese.
Cover and bake at
400° until mixture is steaming.
Remove cover, reduce heat to 350° and bake about 30 to 45 minutes or until eggplant is tender and sauce thick.

title: afternoon delight
directions: Blend margarine, flour and all but 1/4 cup pecans.
Spread in bottom of a glass serving dish about 13 x 8 1/2.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool completely.

title: rosa's macaroni pie
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
While still hot, add the margarine and all but 1/2 cup cheese; mix well.
Beat the eggs and add to macaroni mixture.
Add milk and seasonings.
Return to stove; cook, stirring, over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese has melted (about 20 minutes).
Children's favorite!

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour on cake layer.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn down to 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate nut bread
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Mix milk, sugar, oleo and egg in bowl until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 50 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen sides from pan.
Remove.
Cool before slicing.
Store tightly wrapped.

title: hash browns au gratin
directions: Pour 1 stick of melted butter on potatoes.
Mix together chicken soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
(Add to potatoes and stir).
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with corn flake crumbs, mixed with 1/2 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: golden glow punch
directions: In punch bowl, mix lemonade, Sauterne, curacao and brandy. Stir in club soda and ice cubes.
Serve in punch cups.

title: sugar-free applesauce cake
directions: Cook raisins in water.	Let cool completely.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Add raisins and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon nuts
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, water and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and stir occasionally.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Stir until mixture becomes candied.
Separate and pour onto waxed paper.

title: oriental pork steaks
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Heat.
Place meat in pan.
Poke holes.
Cover meat with mixture and marinate overnight.
Grill 10 to 15 minutes or until done, brushing with honey mixture.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cover sliced squash with water and boil for 5 minutes. Drain. Mix squash, stuffing and onion. Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and place half this mixture in it. Set the rest aside.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat sugar, margarine and shortening until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix sour cream and milk; reserve.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and/or noodles.
Brown meat and onion; add salt and pepper.
Mix hamburger, paste, pizza sauce, tomato sauce, paste and sugar.
Add spices to suit to taste.
Place in casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cracker dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Combine rice, seasoning packet from rice mix and hot water. Place in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside. Sprinkle pork chops with pepper and place over rice mixture.

title: poor man's caviar
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

Bake eggplant on rack in center of oven for 1/2 hour, turning it over once or twice, until soft and its skin is charred and blistered. Cook onions in 4 tablespoons oil over moderate heat for 6 to 8 minutes,
until soft, but not brown. Stir in green pepper and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.

title: chicken breast scampi
directions: Cut chicken breasts into approximately 2 ounce chunks and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Add garlic, scallions, parsley, dill, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat for 2 minutes, then pour the mixture over the chicken.
I always melt the butter and cook the ingredients for 2 minutes in the microwave.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Separate chicken pieces and cook for another 10 minutes.
Turn on the broiler to brown chicken for 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve over rice or thin spaghetti.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Boil margarine, water, oil and cocoa.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Mix together and add buttermilk with soda and 2 eggs plus vanilla.
Bake in 18 x 12-inch foil-lined jelly roll pan at 385° for 20 minutes.
Frost immediately.

title: apple cider
directions: Heat to boil.
Don't let it boil.
Turn off heat.
Leave sit overnight.
Slice an orange and lemon to float.

title: grouper parmesan
directions: Combine lemon juice and sherry.
Combine breadcrumbs, cheese, lemon rind and garlic powder.
Rinse fillets with cold water; pat dry.
Dip fillets in lemon juice mixture, then roll in breadcrumb mixture.
Place fillets in a vegetable spray coated 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining breadcrumb mixture over fillets.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Serves 4.

title: gratin potatoes
directions: Layer potato slices in buttered 13 x 9 baking dish, Stir together cream, garlic, salt and pepper. Pour over
potatoes. Bake at 400 degrees for 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender and mixture is bubbly and golden. Let stand 15 minutes before serving. Yields 8 servings.

title: onion potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag, add oil and potatoes (cut up) and soup mix.
Close bag and evenly toss. Empty into baking dish.
Bake and stir about 40 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
In a separate mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and powdered sugar. Blend until smooth.
Add Dream Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill several hours.

title: dill pickles
directions: Cut pickles into 1/4 inch slices.
Pack loosely into sterilized Ball jars.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag.
Add to sugar and vinegar.
Bring mixture to boil.
Cool to room temperature.
Remove spice bag.
Pour syrup over pickle slices. Adjust caps.
To develop flavor, store in refrigerator 1 week before using.
Yields about 2 pints.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Soften cream and beat in egg until smooth. Add chocolate chips.
Set aside.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in water until done.
Remove chicken from bones, put chicken back in water.
Add soup and mix well.
Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Bring soup to a full boil.
Add bouillon cubes and drop biscuits into boiling soup.
Stir until done.

title: white fudge
directions: Cook to soft boil.
Let cool.
Add 1 cup nuts and beat until of spreading consistency.
Butter hands and make into a flat loaf. Slice when firm.

title: peanut butter fudge candy(microwave)
directions: In mixing bowl, melt butter on High for 45 seconds.
Add sugar, cocoa, salt and milk.
Cook on High, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 12 x 7-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool several hours at room temperature or in refrigerator.
This candy freezes well.

title: shrimp wreck beer boil
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil. Devein shrimp and shell. Add shrimp; boil only a few minutes, until the shrimp begin to turn pink. Drain the liquid and serve on tray with your favorite shrimp sauce.

title: lemon-orange pound cake
directions: Blend until smooth, about 3 minutes.
Bake in greased tube pan 1 hour at 350°.
Then glaze immediately.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Put melted butter over bread cubes.
Mix sugar, orange, lemon and puree together.
Pour over cubes; combine.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Add cooked rice, meat, grated onion, garlic, salt, pepper and crushed mint in a large mixing bowl and mix thoroughly.
Remove stem from grape leaf; lay flat on plate.
Place a roll of mixture on bottom of leaf and roll.
Turn ends of leaf in and finish rolling.
Finished roll should be 3 x 3/4-inch roughly.
Place side by side in baking dish.
Add lemon and water.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes about 20 rolls.
(For larger amount, rolls may be layered, but keep covered with water and lemon juice.
Great for parties.

title: michigan sauce
directions: In a medium to large heated frypan, mix together tomato sauce, garlic powder, black pepper, chili powder, cumin, hot sauce and cinnamon.
Insure all is mixed well.
Add raw hamburg; cook slowly until done.
Makes enough for 15 to 20 hot dogs.

title: knorr spinach dip
directions: Mix all above ingredients, making sure cream cheese is soft enough to blend.
Serve with dipping chips.

title: pinata double dip
directions: In a skillet, mix all the ingredients together well.
Heat over low heat until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
May be served on a food warmer, or preheated serving bowl.

title: chicken delights
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese until blended.
Slice chicken breasts in thin slices while still half frozen.
Make small balls out of blended butter and cream cheese.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Wrap chicken slices around balls (use beaten egg white to help keep together).
Dip chicken balls in egg whites and then in flour mixture.
Fry in deep fat until brown and done.
(If necessary, use more cheese, butter and egg white.)
Serve warm.

title: cream of crawfish soup
directions: Place crawfish tails in a blender and process until they are pureed; set aside.
Melt butter; add flour, stir and cook for about 5 minutes (do not brown).
Add onions and cook until tender. Add pureed crawfish tails, stirring and cooking for 5 minutes. Slowly add cream and water, stirring constantly.
Add paprika, cayenne pepper, salt and parsley.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes on a slow flame.
Serves 16 as appetizer (demitasse) or 6 to 8 for cups of soups.

title: mom's white lite cake
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar and oil; beat well with spoon.
Add milk, vanilla, baking powder, salt and 1 cup of flour.
Alternate (milk, flour) until mixed thoroughly, then the second cup of flour. Beat with electric beaters.
Grease and line 9 x 13-inch pan with parchment paper or wax paper.
With rubber spatula, fold into pan.
Bake at 325° to 330° approximately 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Top with your favorite topping.
Ideal for shortcakes also.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each addition.
Add vanilla wafer crumbs and milk alternately.
Add coconut and pecans; fold into batter.
Bake in a tube pan sprayed with "Baker's Joy" at 275° for about 1 1/4 hours. (Freezes well.)

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix all together well and keep in covered bowl in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.
To make, fill paper muffin cups 3/4 full and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: 24 hour stew
directions: Mix good.
Put in a cool place.
Better after 24 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Rinse beans and add 2 quarts cold water.
Bring to boil, then simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover.
Let stand for 1 hour or add beans to water and soak overnight.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to beans and soaking water.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Add sugar, mustard, molasses, pork or bacon, beans and onions into a casserole dish.
Bake 5 to 7 hours at 300°.
Add more liquid, if necessary.
Serves 8.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage, onion and pepper; drain. Mix with remaining ingredients. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. This recipe freezes well.

title: apple pie(no sugar)
directions: Bring cornstarch in apple juice to a boil and cook until it thickens.
Add cinnamon and butter or margarine.
Mix into chopped apples.
Bake in 2 crust pie.
This is good with any kind of frozen berries or fruit.
Also good using the thickened apple juice in a 1 crust pie, leaving the berries uncooked.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Blend rice, creamed soups and water; spread in well-greased flat casserole.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice and soup mixture.
Top with 1 envelope dry onion soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Don't peek!

title: swiss ham pie(quiche)
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter (or margarine); blend in flour and nutmeg.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Cool slightly. Stir small amount of cheese sauce into eggs.
Return egg mixture to cheese sauce; add ham.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients, except cake mix, then add cake mix and blend. Mix 1 tablespoon cinnamon and 3 tablespoons brown sugar. Grease and flour a tube pan. Pour a thin layer of the cake mixture into pan and sprinkle with a layer of sugar-cinnamon mixture. Repeat this twice, ending with a layer of cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let cake cool before taking out of pan.

title: cherry delight dessert
directions: Mix crumbs with sugar; pour melted butter over mixture and toss lightly.
Pat firmly over entire bottom of a 9-inch pan. Cream the cheese, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Beat until fluffy, blend in prepared topping and spread over crumb crust.
Pour pie filling over topping.
Chill 8 hours or overnight.

title: strawberry-spinach salad
directions: Snap off and discard woody bases from asparagus.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Add asparagus and water to 1-quart microwave-safe baking dish.
Stirring once, cook, covered, on High, until tender-crisp, 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain, rinse with cold water.
Let stand in cold water until cool; drain.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Cut steak in 1/2-inch strips, removing all fat and bone. Place meat in skillet, sprayed with Pam.
Also, add the onion. Brown lightly, stirring often.
Add the soy sauce, one can of soup and 3/4 can of water.
Cook in the skillet on low until meat is tender and gravy is thickened.
Serve this over egg noodles or rice.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop up stems from mushrooms and saute with garlic in butter. Mix with rest of the ingredients; stuff the mushrooms.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine peanut butter, oleo, and sugars. Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Sprinkle chips on top.
Place in a 350° oven for 3 minutes. Remove from oven.
Run knife through to marbelize.
Return to oven and bake for 20 minutes.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Mix brownies according to package directions.
Add chocolate morsels.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan for 30 minutes.
(I use aluminum pan.)

title: homemade sausage
directions: Put the pork through meat grinder with the sage, red pepper, black pepper and salt.
Mix well by hand.
When ready to cook, form into patties and fry until cooked through and well browned.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers into jars.
Heat vinegar, water and salt. Bring to a rolling boil and pour over cucumbers.
Seal.

title: pineapple cream tv cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese (softened) and 2 cups milk.
Add pudding (dry) mix.
Spread over cake.
Drain pineapple.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Cover with cream and sprinkle with coconut or nuts.
Refrigerate 1 hour or more.

title: mildred's hot rolls
directions: Mix 2 cups flour and yeast together in a bowl.
In a pan, heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt just until warm and stir constantly.
Add the milk mixture to flour mixture, then add the egg.
Beat with a hand mixer on low speed for 1/2 minute. Beat 3 minutes on high. Stir in remaining flour and mix with a spoon. Knead on a floured board 5 minutes.
Shape into a ball and place in bowl. Cover.
Let rise 1 hour.
Punch down. Shape into rolls. Place in greased baking pan.
Let rise again for 30 minutes. Bake at 400° until brown. Brush with butter.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt. Add butter. Stir until combined. Press onto bottom and up the sides of a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Pour pie filling into crust. In a mixing

bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla until smooth. Spread around outside edges of pie, leaving a 3-inch circle of cherries in the center. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until edges begin to brown. Cool. Refrigerate for several hours before serving. Serves 8.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar well.
Add eggs and mix until creamy. Add sour cream.
Mix flour with next 4 ingredients. Mix with the butter mixture.
Pour batter into prepared 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Mix the brown sugar, nuts, and cinnamon well.
sprinkle over top. Cover, chill 8 hours.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 35-45 minutes. Yield 12 servings.

title: chocolate graham cracker pie
directions: Line bottom of 8 x 8-inch cake pan with graham crackers (about 4 1/2 crackers).
Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Put pudding on top of graham crackers.
Place in refrigerator.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add soup and desired amount of potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: help!
directions: Mix mustard and catsup until you have good tasting sauce.
Add dash of Tabasco.
(Use more catsup than mustard.)
Cut meat into bite sizes and using toothpicks dip into sauce.
Can be served hot or cold.
Serve with any handy cracker.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Dissolve orange jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Take out 1/2 cup and mix with 1 cup sour cream.
Stir well.
Pour sour cream/jello mixture in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
(Reserve 1 1/2 cups jello.)
Put in refrigerator.
Chill until set.
Pour on reserved jello.
Chill until set.
Repeat with remaining colors of jello.

title: oriental pork tenderloins
directions: Note:
good for diabetics or high cholesterol or if you are watching calories.

title: squash relish
directions: Dice squash, onion, peppers and pimentos. Put in a large bowl and add seeds. Combine sugar and vinegar; pour over ingredients and let stand 1 hour. Then bring to a boil for 5 minutes. Makes about 6 pints.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except for the 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/3 cup margarine and 1 cup flour.
Mix these 3 ingredients together until crumbly.
Spread potato mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour over 10 ounces of broken hard pretzels.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Stir halfway through baking.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: coney island sauce
directions: In large skillet, combine beef, onion and garlic; cook until browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes.
Spoon over hot dogs in buns.
Refrigerate or freeze leftovers.

title: christmas recipe
directions: Place all ingredients in house a few weeks before Christmas. Sprinkle with secrets and allow time to simmer.
Gradually add patience to Mother as needed.
Add as much joy, laughter and faith as hearts will hold.
Garnish with unpaid bills.
Serve generous portions topped with the blessings and love of the Christ Child. There will be plenty to go around and lots of leftovers for yourself.

title: wassail
directions: Heat in covered pan until steaming.
Cover and steep for 10 minutes.
Serve with rum.

title: harvey wallbanger cake(excellent)
directions: Mix everything together in large bowl. Beat 4 minutes. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.

title: cottage cheese
directions: Mix ingredients together and set aside for 18 to 24 hours or until mixture clabbers.
Stir, then heat 20 to 30 minutes over low heat.
Stir occasionally.
After whey separates, strain off from curds; discard whey.
Mix in 1 teaspoon of salt and 1 to 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine while curds are warm.
Serve immediately or chill before serving.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown 1 pound ground meat, onion, green pepper and jalapenos. Mix remaining ingredients into batter.
Spread a layer of 1/2 batter, meat, then remaining batter.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Mix
dissolved	yeast,	sugar, eggs and warm water in a very large
bowl.
Add
oil, salt and flour.
Mix well.	Cover the bowl with a cloth and let it stand 8 hours or overnight on the counter (not in the refrigerator).	Divide the dough in 3 parts.
Roll each
part	into
a
circular shape on a floured surface.
Cut each
circle
into	8 parts.
Roll large end of each triangle into small end.	Place on ungreased pan, shaping each piece
in	a crescent.
Let rise 6 hours.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: chinese cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, apple, carrot and onions and mix well.
Cover with dressing, mix well and serve.
Serves about 6.
You can also add a small zucchini (chop fine).

title: truffle
directions: Cut angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Make pudding according to directions.
Beat whipping cream on high until creamy. Add pudding to whipped cream; stir until smooth.
Add in almond extract.
Place cake in center of bowl.
Place cherries around edges.
Next, add cream on top.
Layer 3 times the cake, cherries and pudding; end with pudding on top.
Refrigerate for 5 hours and serve.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Blend in egg yolk and vanilla.
Add dry cake mix 1/3 at a time, mixing well after each addition.
(If mixer is used, add last 1/3 by hand.)
Cover and chill 30 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed; rinse and cool.
Mix in remaining ingredients.

title: baked lobster and shrimp casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs; place in individual baking shells.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: crab mornay
directions: Melt butter in pot and saute onions and parsley.
Blend in flour, cream, and cheese until cheese is melted.
Add other ingredients and gently add crabmeat.
Serve on melba toast or crackers.

title: mother's chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken.
When cool, remove skin and fat, then cut chicken in small pieces.
Using broth from cooking chicken, make enough thick gravy to cover chicken.
Mix chicken with gravy. Season with black pepper and additional salt, if needed.
Add melted butter.
Line 10-inch deep pie dish with pie crust; pour in chicken mixture.
Cover with pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.
If desired, serve with additional gravy.
This dish was mother's favorite to serve for special occasions.

title: dreams
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Roll in superfine sugar while warm.

title: huckleberry cobbler
directions: Divide pie crust in two equal parts.
Put one in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare huckleberries (wild blueberries) with 2 cups water and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Cook until very hot and sugar dissolves.
Pour over crust. Top with second crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve with ice cream,
hot or cold, so good!!

title: frozen cucumbers 2
directions: Sprinkle salt over pickles.
Let stand for 2 hours and drain. Meanwhile, mix together vinegar and sugar.
Boil mixture until sugar is dissolved and cool.
Pour over drained cucumbers and put in containers and freeze.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add butter, eggs, water, pumpkin and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into 4 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes approximately 1 hour.
Allow to cool.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp, leaving the skin and about 1/2-inch of pulp intact.
Place in mixing bowl; set aside.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and mash (no big chunks).
Add onions, garlic and flour, salt it.
Add garlic powder.
Mix tomato paste with 1 can water.
Mix tomato puree with 2 cans water.
Pour over meat mixture.
Then add sugar and hot sauce, stir well.
Bring to boil. Cook slow.
Stir every 20 minutes.
Cook 6 hours.

title: deviled biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Snip biscuits into quarters. Arrange in two 8-inch round pans. Mix butter and deviled ham, stirring until well blended. Pour over biscuits; sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 40.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix by directions and pour half in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
While this is baking, melt caramels with milk and oleo.
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Pour the rest of the cake mix over the other cake and bake 15 more minutes or until done.

title: smoked salmon roulade
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a 10 x 15-inch jellyroll pan with heavy-duty foil, shiny side up, allowing a 1-inch overlap all around.
Fold overlap around edges firmly.
Brush 1 teaspoon melted butter over foil lined bottom.
Melt remaining 1/4 cup butter in a saucepan and add flour, stirring with a wire whisk.
Add milk, stirring rapidly with whisk, and cook until thickened and smooth. Simmer, stirring, about 1 minute.
Beat egg yolks well in a small mixing bowl and add a little of the hot sauce, beating constantly, off heat.
Add this mixture to the sauce, stirring constantly.
Add salt to the egg whites; beat until stiff and fold into sauce.
Pour batter into pan and smooth the top.
Bake or 15 to 18 minutes or until cake is golden brown and rebounds to the touch.
(If the cake splits on top, don't worry; it will seal itself once it cools.) After cooling, turn the cake onto a clean dish towel.
Carefully remove and discard foil.

title: calico squash casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 8 minutes or until squash is tender; drain.
Saute onion, green pepper and green onions in 1 tablespoon butter until tender; set aside.

title: hot 'n' spicy beef tenderloin roast
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and sprinkle over surface of roast. Insert meat thermometer so bulb is centered into thickest part. Grill 30 to 45 minutes depending on thickness of roast.
Turn 2 or 3 times.
Remove roast when meat thermometer registers 135°.
Allow to stand 15 minutes.
Carve into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Garnish with fresh herbs.
This recipe also good with pork.

title: baked chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
Brown on all sides in margarine.
Arrange chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir soup into butter in skillet; slowly stir in chicken broth.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Pour over chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 35 minutes more.

title: kentucky bourbon sweet potatoes
directions: Turn sweet potatoes into large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until heated through.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash sweet potatoes.
Add sugar, bourbon, butter and vanilla; beat until well blended. Turn into 2-quart, shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle marshmallows over top.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes, or until marshmallows are golden.
Serves 9.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain.
Mix spaghetti sauce, cottage cheese, 1/2 the Parmesan cheese and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese together.
Mix noodles with the sauce in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with the remaining cheese.
Microwave 8 minutes or bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: beet relish
directions: Cook beets until tender and the skins slip off easily.
Cut or chop the beets, onion and peppers.
Combine the ingredients. Cook the mixture until it is clear.
Seal it in clean, hot jars.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: In large bowl combine peas, beans, corn, onion, celery and pimentos.
In a saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Heat and stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over the vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: best ever banana pudding
directions: Combine melted margarine, brown sugar, flour, salt, evaporated milk, water, eggs and vanilla in double boiler; mix well.
Cook until thickened, stirring frequently.
Reserve 2 to 3 vanilla wafers.
Layer banana slices, pudding and vanilla wafers alternately in large bowl.
Crumble reserved wafers over top. Cover with whipped topping.
Chill, covered, overnight.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: old-fashioned potato salad
directions: Mix together potato, celery, green onion, radish and parsley. Toss with mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper until well covered.
Chill.
Makes 8 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot sausage dry with paper towels. Combine with cheeses, salad dressing, olives and red pepper. Lightly grease muffin tins and press 1 wrapper in each cup.
Brush lightly with oil.
Bake 5 minutes until golden.
Remove from tins and place on baking sheet.
Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake 5 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix all together in broiler and cook until nuts stop popping. Add 2 teaspoons soda.
Stir quick and pour up very quickly on a greased sheet of foil.
Let cool completely and break into pieces.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.
Can be doubled.

title: acorn elegante
directions: Halve and seed 3 acorn squash.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Saute 2 cups of chopped onions, then add a 6 ounce can of mushrooms.
Stuff the squash, then bake for an additional 20 minutes.
Top with 1 cup of shredded cheese and bake until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all together cold.
Keep refrigerated until used up. Keeps well for weeks.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften and blend margarine, butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours; start in cold oven.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Trim off large leaves of broccoli.
Remove tough ends of lower stalks.
Wash broccoli.
Separate flowerets and coarsely chop stalks.
Bring water to a boil; add salt and broccoli.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain. Set aside.
Combine soup and next 5 ingredients, mixing well. Fold in broccoli; pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Combine stuffing and melted margarine.
Sprinkle around edges of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: portuguese eggs(great brunch dish)
directions: In a greased 13 x 9-inch dish, layer cubed bread, then cubed sausage, then cheese.
Mix milk, eggs and mustard and pour over layers.
Cover and keep in fridge until you're ready to cook.

title: penuche nuts
directions: Combine sugars with sour cream, stirring well.
Stir over low heat until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until mixture coats nuts. Turn out on waxed paper.
Separate with a fork.

title: dream pie
directions: Pour lemon juice in Eagle Brand milk and stir well with spoon. Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add pecans and pineapple.
Pour into crusts and chill until set.

title: veal patty scallopini
directions: Combine the egg, milk, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Add ground veal; mix well.
Shape mixture into 6 patties; coat with flour.
In skillet, brown patties in hot Crisco; drain off fat. Combine tomato sauce, undrained mushrooms, water, parsley, crushed oregano and garlic powder; pour over meat.
Cover; simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: deer stew
directions: Cook stew beef until tender.
Add potatoes, onions, tomatoes, carrots and celery.
Cook until potatoes, carrots and celery are tender.
Add salt, pepper, hot sauce and package of stew mix.
Let simmer for 20 or 30 minutes, stirring while simmering.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add taco seasoning and set aside. Combine Jiffy mix, eggs, oil and corn.
In lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan, put half of the cornbread mixture.
Cover this with the hamburger.
Sprinkle tomatoes and cheese over the hamburger. Top with remaining cornbread.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Roll into balls.
Freeze overnight and then bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti in lightly salted water until tender; drain. Combine with remaining ingredients, reserving half the cheese; pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Mix sugars, flour and cornmeal.
Beat eggs slightly; add to this mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in milk and margarine or butter. Add vanilla and vinegar; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Fill cup with
raisins	and
cover with hot water.
Mix everything together; pour into greased pan.
Bake in slow oven until done.

title: stuffed cabbages
directions: With sharp knife, cut deep around stem of cabbage.
Place stem up in large kettle with about 2 inches of water.
Cover and bring to a boil.
As leaves start to wilt, remove with a fork to colander and drain.
