There should be approximately 24 leaves. Chop some of remaining cabbage to get 1/2 c.
Set aside.

title: bacalhau a' gomes de sa'(stockfish recipe)
directions: Wash the fish thoroughly in several changes of water.
Soak the fish overnight in water to cover; drain well.
Add fresh water to cover.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Drain, reserving the liquid.
Remove the skin and bones carefully.
Shred the fish coarsely.
Cook the unpeeled potatoes in the fish stock until tender, about 30 minutes.
Peel and slice thin.
Heat the olive oil in a frying pan.
Add the onions and garlic.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add fish and potatoes.
Cook over high heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the pepper and white wine and stir.
Place the mixture in a buttered baking dish or casserole. Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Chop 3 of the eggs coarsely and slice the other 3.
Garnish with eggs and parsley.

title: birda's decorated cabbage
directions: Wash and peel outer leaves of cabbage.
Cut center flat. Set on
large platter.
Arrange and pierce layer by layer, bits of cheese,
olives
and
vegetables
with toothpicks to form a crown of appetizers.
Great for parties.

title: snow ball cake
directions: Soak gelatine in cold water. Add boiling water to dissolve. Add orange and lemon juice. Add sugar and mix well. Chill until partly jelled. Whip 1/2 pint cream until stiff. Add 1 tsp. sugar to whipped cream. Mix whipped cream with partially jelled gelatin. Break up angel food cake until bite sized pieces. Line large mixing bowl with waxed paper. Put a layer of cake and layer of gelatin mixture. Add layer of each until all used up. Let set in refrigerator until jelled. Unmold on cake plate. Whip 2nd 1/2 pint cream until stiff adding 1 tsp sugar spread on cake. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: delicious jello salad
directions: Drain fruit (save juice).
Arrange fruit in approximately 9 x 9-inch dish.
Put grapes and apples on top.
Dissolve Jell-O, using 2 cups fruit juice and 1 cup water.
Pour Jell-O over fruit until covered (some may be left over).
Chill.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and
butter
in a mixing bowl either with a mixer or by hand.
Add eggs, one at a time until well blended. Sift flour, soda,
salt,
baking
powder
twice	in a separate container before adding to mixture.
Add a little at a time to mixture until all
is gone, then add sour cream and flavoring. If mixture is too
thick
you	may add a little milk and blend until smooth.

title: pizza spaghetti
directions: Combine cheeses and set aside.
Combine ground beef and salt; saute until meat is done, stirring to crumble well.
Add onion and saute until tender; drain well.
Stir in tomato paste, water, mushrooms and oregano.

title: angel cookies
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Combine the remaining ingredients. Mix together and drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake.
Or roll out.
Add enough flour to roll and cut out cookies.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook onion in hot fat until tender.
Add meat and brown.
Add seasonings, drained beans and soup.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spoon mashed potatoes over meat mixture.
Leave an area in the center uncovered.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Drain artichoke hearts; chop in food processor.
Place chopped hearts in bowl.
Add all other ingredients; blend.
Place in glass pie plate.
Bake until golden brown at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool; serve slightly warm.
Spread over Stoned Wheat Thins and enjoy.

title: english lemon pecan tea loaf
directions: Beat butter 30 seconds until soft.
Add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Beat well after each.
Stir in pecans and lemon peel.

title: crab salad(krabbesalat)
directions: Mix mayonnaise with vinegar, salt and paprika to taste.
Add tomato puree, then crabmeat and celery.
Neatly slice tops off tomatoes and scoop out seeds.
Fill with salad and sprinkle alfalfa sprouts on top.

title: icebox hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients with enough buttermilk to make soft batter, not too thin. Drop by teaspoonfuls in hot grease.
Batter will keep in refrigerator up to 5 days.

title: angie's eggrolls
directions: Brown meat, drain.
Add vegetables and stir-fry.
Scramble eggs and pour into mixture.
Mix all together, continue cooking for about 5 minutes.
Spoon mixture into wrappers.
Roll, wet fingers to seal filled wrappers.
Deep fry.
Use with Dynasty Plum Sauce.

title: three layer butter cake
directions: Butter should be softened at room temperature.
Sift plain flour before measuring.
Cream butter well.
Add sugar; cream thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Slowly add flour and baking powder.
Add milk and vanilla extract.
Increase speed on mixer and beat for several minutes.
Pour into well-greased layer pans.
Bake at 325°.
Frost with your favorite frosting or jelly.

title: quick chili
directions: Put all ingredients in big pan; cook for 45 minutes.
Fry hamburger and onion first.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Scramble beef and drain.
Add soup, water, tomato sauce and brown sugar.
Simmer until hot.
Cook macaroni in separate pan. Mix sauce with noodles and serve.

title: honey-pecan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir contents of vegetable seasoning packet, margarine and water in a bowl to melt margarine.
Add 1/2 cup orange juice, stuffing crumbs and pecans; stir just to moisten.
Mix honey and 2 tablespoons orange juice.
Arrange chicken in a single layer in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon 1/2 of honey mixture over chicken.
Press 1/2 cup stuffing on each chicken breast and wrap with 1 slice bacon.
Spoon remaining mixture over chicken.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup peanut butter and Hershey syrup together into a very thick paste.
Spread onto graham cracker crust.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add rest of peanut butter and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate or freeze.
For a garnish, decorate with chocolate chips.

title: banana nugget cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding chips last.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thoroughly cream margarine, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients. Blend into creamed mixture.
Shape in 1-inch balls and place, 2 inches apart, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Crisscross with a fork, slightly floured.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Cool.
In medium bowl, beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, cornstarch and salt; beat until smooth.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Gradually add evaporated milk and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes until top is puffed.
If top browns too quickly, cover last 15 minutes with foil.

title: apple fluff
directions: Pour applesauce into a bowl and add rind and nutmeg.
Beat egg whites until frothy with cream of tartar.
Slowly add brown sugar and beat until whites peak.
Add 1/3 egg whites to applesauce, folding in slowly, then fold in remainder.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk over low heat, stirring until smooth. Combine remaining milk, cake mix and margarine; mix well. Press half of cake mixture into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle 1 cup chopped walnuts and chocolate pieces over crust and top with melted caramel mixture; spread to edges of pan. Top with teaspoonfuls of remaining cake mix and press into caramel mixture. Sprinkle with remaining walnuts, pressing lightly into top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool slightly and refrigerate. Chocolate may be substituted for German chocolate. Yields approximately 2 dozen cookies.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 9 x 13-inch ovenproof glass baking dish.
Combine soup and sour cream in medium bowl.
Arrange half of potatoes in prepared dish.
Season with salt and pepper. Pour half of soup mixture over potatoes.
Top with remaining potatoes.
Pour remaining soup mixture over.
Season to taste with salt and freshly ground pepper.
Bake until golden brown, 90 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat well and add 1 can chopped shrimp, drained.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except boiling water.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes. Remove from mixer and stir in boiling water.
(Batter will be thin.)
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch or three 8-inch layer pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers, 35 to 40 minutes for 13 x 9-inch pan or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes on rack.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: barbecued lima beans
directions: Soak dried limas overnight.
Boil until tender with ham bone or salt pork.
Try out some salt pork in frying pan.
Put 1 clove garlic and 1 onion (sliced) in fat and brown.
Add 1 teaspoon salt, tomato soup, mustard, sugar and vinegar; stir and cook slowly 15 minutes.
Put limas in layers alternately with sauce in casserole. Put browned squares of salt pork on top.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: ham salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If you wish, a little celery seed may also be added to this.

title: pork roast
directions: Wash pork roast and season with salt and pepper. Place in roasting pan. Mix sugar with Coke and pour over roast. Cover with foil and bake in slow oven (325° to 350°) for about 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until tender.

title: barbecued beef short ribs
directions: Brown short ribs in oil; pour off excess fat.
Place in pressure cooker.
Add water and remaining ingredients.
Cover; set control at 10 and cook 45 to 50 minutes after the steam is up. Remove from heat and cool down.
Thicken the sauce with 1 tablespoon flour mixed with 1/4 cup water for each cup of sauce. Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Juice from the can of pineapple is the liquid for this cake. Mix in bowl by hand (not mixer). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased pan and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple pie
directions: Slice apples.
Mix together sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt. Sprinkle over apples.
Slice butter on top of pie.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: beef stock
directions: Put last 3 ingredients in cheesecloth bag.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook shanks in a baking pan in oven until brown.
Drain off and discard fat.
Place all ingredients in large stock pot. Simmer 2 hours, skimming off foam as it raises to surface.
Strain through a cheesecloth-lined strainer.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove and discard congealed fat from surface.
Use within 3 days or freeze.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: egg custard
directions: Warm all this on top of stove until butter melts.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water and chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped topping with electric beater and lemon pie filling.
Now stir in oranges.
Chill overnight.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix and chill at least 1 hour.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat tomato soup (do not boil).
Add gelatin in a little cold water and the salt.
Mix separately the mayonnaise, softened cream cheese, celery and onion.
Set aside.
Drain and chop the shrimp. Combine the soup and shrimp, then mix in the other ingredients. Line a mold with plastic wrap and pour mixture.
Chill.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix eggs, pumpkin, oil and water.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake in 3 well-greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in pans.

title: oven orange chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in small bowl and dip the chicken pieces into mixture, coating completely.
Lay in single layer in baking dish. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and place orange slices over each piece, if desired. Bake 15 minutes longer, uncovered.

title: yellow-pineapple cake
directions: Bake as directed on box at 350° for 32 to 35 minutes. Cool cake completely.

title: white chili
directions: The night before, place beans in a large pot or bowl.
Cover amply with cold water and let soak overnight.
Drain the beans the following day.

title: cream cheese dessert
directions: Cream	cream	cheese	and
sugar
together.
Dissolve gelatine in hot water; add 7-Up and lemon juice.
Add to cream cheese mixture;
mix
well.
Mix
in peaches, Mandarin oranges and peach syrup
to cheese mixture.
Pour into a lightly oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: sour cream chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Dredge chicken pieces in flour.
In skillet, heat margarine and brown chicken on all sides.
Transfer pieces to casserole.
Add mushrooms and mixture of sour crem and water.
Sprinkle with thyme and chives (or onions).
Cover well and bake until tender, about 1 hour.
Serves well with fluffy rice. Serves 4.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix ingredients by hand.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: aunt rose's zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, baking soda, zucchini, raisins and nuts.
In another bowl, beat together the eggs, vanilla and oil.
Pour over flour mixture; stir until thoroughly mixed.
Turn into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, onions and sausage until brown; drain.
Cook pepperoni; put on paper towel and blot off excess grease.
Cook noodles for just a few minutes and drain.
Layer ingredients as follows:
hamburger mixture, noodles, pepperoni, pizza sauce, cheese.
Continue to layer until finished.
Always end with cheese on top layer.
If this mixture appears dry, put more sauce on or some milk.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed.
Mix well.
Spoon by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Lightly grease pie pan.
In a saucepan, steam broccoli until almost tender. Drain well.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain and reserve
liquid.
Melt
butter
in saucepan over low heat; add flour
and
stir
until
blended and smooth but not brown. Add onion and cook until soft but not brown.
Add milk and 1/2 cup spinach
liquid slowly stirring constantly to avoid lumps. Cook until
smooth and thick.
Continue stirring.
Add seasonings and cheese which has
been
cut
into small pieces.
Stir until melted and combine
with
cooked
spinach.
This
may be served immediately or put
into
casserole
and
topped
with buttered bread crumbs.
Can
be frozen and reheated.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: apples for fried pies
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.
Then cook 1 hour over medium heat or cook until done.
(Tastes like dried apples.) Freeze or put into hot jars of size desired.
Process pints 15 minutes in boiling water.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put Veg-All in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups together with salt and pepper.
Spread over Veg-All.
Then mix flour, milk and mayonnaise and spread over soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: bran muffins(makes 24)
directions: Mix cereal, milk, oil and eggs.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add carrots, raisins and nuts.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chinese crispy wontons
directions: Combine pork, water chestnuts, green onions, soy sauce, corn starch, salt and ginger in a medium bowl.
Mix well.
Place 1/2 tsp. of pork mixture in the center of each wonton skin.
Fold wonton skin over filling and form a triangle.
Turn top of triangle down to meet fold.
Turn over moisten 1 corner with water.
Overlap opposite corner over moistened corner.
Press together firmly.
Heat oil in wok or large sauce pan to 375F. Deep fry wontons 3-4 at a time for 2-3 minutes or until brown and crispy.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with spicy mustard or sweet & sour sauce.

title: breakfast surprise
directions: Layer bread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (greased).
Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together with salt and pepper.
Pour over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes.
Slice.
Is better if mixed and put in fridge overnight before baking.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Open pie crust, warm up hot fudge topping to work with.
Spoon some in bottom of crust and on sides.
Get ice cream soft enough to work with.
Spoon ice cream into crust.
Put into freezer, harden for 20 to 30 minutes or until hard.
Put more topping on top then serve.

title: english muffin pizzas
directions: Take 1/2 of muffin and add sauce.
Add pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese.
Take the other half and do the same.
Place each muffin on tray and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Make crust.
Follow directions on box for Dream Whip.
Add cream cheese and powdered sugar to Dream Whip and beat until smooth.
Put graham cracker crust on bottom.
Add layer of cheese mixture, then blueberries.
Continue layers and place in refrigerator to set for several hours.

title: everlasting slaw
directions: Combine the cabbage, pepper and sugar and mix well.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil.
Pour boiling mixture over cabbage mixture.
Store in refrigerator in covered container.
Keeps at least 4 weeks.

title: barbara's peanut patties
directions: Mix first four ingredients and boil until forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add butter and vanilla and beat with wooden spoon until thick; pour into greased muffin tins.

title: avocado salsa
directions: Mix together and serve with chips.

title: hot and spicy chili
directions: In a frying pan saute the onion and green pepper in 1/2 stick of butter.
When done, set aside.
Brown hamburger meat and drain off grease.
Add all ingredients to a large pot and cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until you desire.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, water and brown sugar.
Layer sliced potatoes and pour hot syrup over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix all together and pour into pastry shells. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: frosted coffee and raisin squares
directions: Put the soda in the warm coffee, then melt margarine in coffee also. Cook raisins just a little in hot water in microwave or on top of stove.
Place brown sugar in
mixing bowl. Add coffee mixture and egg.
Beat.
Mix together and add the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Add raisins.
Spread in a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: barbeque sauce
directions: Mix in small saucepan.	If you like a hotter taste, add a little
hot sauce or more cayenne.	Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour, vanilla, salt and soda; beat well.
Add diced apples and small jar maraschino cherries and 1 cup Angel Flake coconut or 1 cup nuts. Cook in cake pan or angel food pan.
Keeps really good - moist.

title: punch
directions: Add enough water to make 4 gallons and sweeten to taste.

title: the recipe
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown meat, onion and green pepper. Add tomato sauce and tomato soup.
Add all other ingredients, except English peas.
Simmer.
Just before taking up, add peas. Mix all with pasta.
Put in a baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry what's it cake
directions: Place 1 bag of miniature marshmallows on bottom of 9 x 13 pan (ungreased).
Make yellow cake mix.
Pour batter on top of marshmallows.
Cut strawberries.
Mash, sweeten and add 1 box strawberry Jell-O (dry).
Pour strawberry mixture on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes (it may take longer).

title: cabbage soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cook until cabbage is tender.

title: chip dip
directions: Cream all together.
Chill and serve with chips or crackers.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in jellyroll pan, making sure all of the seams are pinched together.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until a light golden brown.
While crust is baking, mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix together.
Spread this mixture on the cooked crust.
Spread the various vegetables over the cheese mixture.
Cover with waxed paper and gently press the veggies into the cheese mixture.
(This keeps the veggies in place while eating them!)
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Cut into squares for serving time.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Lightly beat the eggs, add the vanilla and combine with the first mixture.
Add the oats and beat again.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
These cookies may be made into drop cookies, or you may wish to add extra flour and form into rolls and refrigerate.
After chilling, cut into slices and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sugar cream pie(my mother-in-law's recipe)
directions: Mix together in pan.
A little at a time, add 1 pint of half and half.
Add butter the size of a walnut.
Bring to boil.
Cook until thick.
Cool slightly.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Melt cream cheese and tomato soup and blend.
Let cool to warm.
Mix Knox gelatine with water and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and place in oiled mold overnight.

title: lucky vanous' chocolate yummy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer crumbs, milk and peanut butter (combined), granola, chocolate chips and then coconut.
Pat down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Cool completely in pan before slicing.

title: woo woo
directions: Add ice cubes.
Shake and pour into glasses.

title: rob's picante sauce
directions: Hot bath and peel tomatoes.
Chop tomatoes (by hand).
Chop other ingredients and add to tomatoes in large pan.
Add vinegar, salt and sugar.
Heat and stir occasionally for 20 minutes.
Fill jars and seal with flats and rings.
Hot bath for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Mix well all ingredients except egg whites.
Place on stove; do not stir while cooking.
Cook until candy forms a hard ball when tested in a cup of cold water.
Remove from heat.
Beat constantly while adding stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Beat.
Drop quickly onto waxed paper.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salted water until tender; drain thoroughly.
In a large skillet, saute onion in 5 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add soup and mix well.
Add cheese; heat and stir until melted.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in cabbage, salt and pepper.
Transfer to an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
In a small skillet, melt remaining butter.
Cook and stir crumbs in butter until lightly browned; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: 10 minute rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and eggs into pudding mix in saucepan. Add rice and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil. Pour into dessert dishes or serving bowl.
Sprinkle with cinnamon when cool.
Makes 8 servings.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Cook vegetables in water and bouillon until tender.
Add milk. Simmer 20 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and margarine.

title: sweet potato pudding pie
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until tender.
Place layers of sliced potatoes in deep dish.
Sprinkle with sugar, butter and spice.
Cover with pie crust.
Make 2 or 3 layers of potatoes and pie crust.
Bake until brown.
Pour milk on top of pie and let come to a boil.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter, add sugar, eggs and pineapple.
Mix well.
Add cubed bread and mix.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: baby wipes
directions: Mix the boiling water with the other ingredients.

title: sweet and sour veggies
directions: Slice all vegetables finely.
Bring sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper to a boil for 4 to 5 minutes.
Pour over vegetables and chill overnight or several hours.

title: playground fun
directions: Mix all ingredients and enjoy!
Please don't leave out any ingredients or you won't be satisfied!

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Work butter until creamy; beat in sugar and eggs, one at a time.
When creamy, fold in flour with spoon.
Spread in buttered, floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: christmas strawberries
directions: Mix and chill for 20 minutes.
Shape into berries (about 1 teaspoon for each berry); roll in red granulated sugar or strawberry Jell-O, sprinkled on foil.
If desired, dye almond slivers green and use 2 or 3 as stem.
Let berries dry several hours.

title: tea scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Chop in butter with pastry blender until flour coated particles of butter are the size of coarse meal.
Add egg and milk.
Stir quickly and lightly until no flour shows.
Turn dough out on a floured surface and knead gently about 15 times.
Cut the dough in half.
Shape each half into a ball and press each down into a round about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut each into 8 wedges like a pie.
Place the wedges on a greased cookie sheet, without allowing the sides to touch.
Glaze, if desired, with lightly beaten egg. Bake until golden brown, about 12 minutes.

title: pistachio dream dessert
directions: Melt butter in glass baking dish.
Sprinkle flour over butter (evenly). Do not stir.
Add 2/3 cup pecans over this.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Take out of oven and cool completely.

title: pineapple nut bars
directions: Mix and press in bottom of ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to directions on box.
Spoon stuffing loosely into pockets of chops.
Place chops in a single layer in a large baking pan (chops should not be touching, use two pans if needed).

title: watercress and pork
directions: Heat pan.
Slightly brown ginger and garlic.
Add pork and fry. Add seasoning and water.
When it comes to a boil, add watercress and cook for 3 minutes or until done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and baking powder.
Fold in butter.
Add egg yolks, beaten.
Press 1/2 batter into pan. Peel and slice medium apples.
Arrange on top of crust.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup flour, 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Crumble remaining batter over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes on small cookie sheet.

title: cherry cream crescents
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and egg yolk. Separate dough into 16 triangles. Place on lightly greased baking sheet. Spread 1 tablespoon of cream cheese mixture near the edge of the short side of each triangle. Top with 1 tablespoon pie filling. Fold long point of triangle over filling and tuck under dough. Lightly beat egg white. Brush over rolls. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 16 rolls.

title: rotel chicken casserole
directions: Boil spaghetti and chicken breasts until done.	Combine Cheez Whiz and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Microwave until cheese is melted.
Then add soup to mixture and dice chicken and add to mixture.
Grease 9 x 13 casserole dish with cooking spray.
Place cooked spaghetti in dish and pour mixture over spaghetti.
Salt and pepper.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake on 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients in mixing bowl until smooth. Arrange fruit on serving platter.
Put dip in pretty bowl and place in center of fruit.

title: wine-poached chicken breasts
directions: Remove excess fat from chicken.
Place chicken and remaining ingredients in a 10-inch nonstick skillet.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until chicken is done, about 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
In a skillet, put cheese, butter, onion and mushroom soup all together; keep stirring.
Arrange broccoli in bottom of casserole; garnish with almond slivers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry sally lunn
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together. Beat eggs and add to mixture. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add this alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Carefully fold in blueberries.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle on batter. Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 50 minutes.
Serve hot; may be reheated.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown meats and onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir in red pepper and oregano. Stir in tomato sauce and Velveeta cheese.
When cheese is melted and well mixed, put about a tablespoon of mix on bread slices.
Put on a cookie sheet and freeze.
When completely frozen, store in a plastic bag and use at your own convenience.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Mix flour and oil until particles are size of small peas. Add water until flour is all moistened and dough cleans side of bowl.
Roll out to fit pan.
Place in pan and crimp edges.
Do not prebake for mince or pumpkin pie.
You would pre-bake for a custard or lemon meringue pie or any pie with a pre-cooked filling.

title: b-b-q roasted venison
directions: Soak deer in
water
enough
to cover meat overnight to which 1/2 of
vinegar
is
added,
pour off water.
Add enough water to cook,
add	pepper,
onion,
celery, garlic and other half of vinegar.
Cook
until well done.
Mix last of ingredients, add water enough
to thin sauce, simmer slowly in oven 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Blend until the appearance of biscuit mix.
Spread half of this mixture on pie shell.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt; add scalded milk and mix well.
Pour small amount over beaten egg yolks; mix well, then return to milk mixture.
Cook in top of double boiler until mixture thickens.
Add butter and vanilla, then pour into prepared pie shell.

title: bob's deluxe chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Arrange chicken in casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover casserole. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix butter or butter and shortening with sugars and eggs until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Slowly add flour, salt and baking soda.
Once mixed, add chocolate chips. Roll dough into small balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: hidden valley dip for vegetables
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: beef with dijon sauce
directions: Cook your roast beef as normal.
Cook sauce until thickened and bubbly.
Pour sauce on meat and serve.

title: cashew crunch
directions: Combine margarine, soy sauce and garlic salt and pour over the top of the first four ingredients.
Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Mix sauce all together.
Pour over chicken and bake in a greased dish at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: butter nutty chews
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°; don't overbake.

title: microwave fudge
directions: *Butterscotch or peanut butter flavored pieces can be substituted for chocolate.

title: strawberry cake
directions: *Drain strawberries and save juice.
If using fresh strawberries, cut into slices and sprinkle with a little sugar and let set long enough to make juice.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, soup and sour cream.
Place in a greased glass 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread butter evenly over top, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add buttermilk and soda, stirred together.
Add baking powder.
Mix and chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: smoked salmon cracker spread
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until light and fluffy (2 to 3 minutes).
Add next 5 ingredients.
By hand, stir in salmon.
Spoon into serving bowl. If desired, garnish with pecans and parsley.
Serve with crackers. Store refrigerated.
Makes 2 cups.

title: special k delights
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over low heat.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and Special K.
Stir until cereal is completely covered.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together, put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cool and even out, pat down.
Save a few crumbs for top.

title: smoked turkey or chicken
directions: Dissolve Tender Quick in water.
Soak turkey in it for 2 days. Make sure turkey is covered (you may have to double or triple recipe).
Use plain water and rub on liquid smoke.
Let stand overnight.

title: cool summer punch
directions: Mix sugar, Kool-Aid and water in jar. Add juices and ginger ale. Mix. Chill, serve and enjoy!

title: (sister) martha's turkey or chicken delight(she brought this to a family reunion and everyone went for it.)
directions: When making dressing, I use a blender to crumb bread and chop celery and onions.
I also try to combine bread types (white bread, biscuits, brown bread, waffles, etc.).

title: peach cream cobbler(100 years old)
directions: Sift flour with one tablespoon sugar and salt.
Cut in butter. Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover crust with remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Mix egg yolks and whipping cream.
Pour over peaches and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: crullers
directions: Mix and fry in hot, deep oil.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt margarine and saute other ingredients.
Add 1 cup water and allow to cook over low heat for about 45 minutes, stirring often to prevent sticking.
Add crawfish, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Thicken if necessary.
Serve over rice. Sprinkle with chopped parsley and green onion tops. 1 pound serves 2 to 3.
